title: mexican bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet with onion, chili powder and garlic powder.
Drain.
Combine cream of chicken with Ro-Tel.
You might add 1/2 can of water to make thinner.
Do this in a separate bowl.
In a large casserole dish, begin making layers in this order:
2 large tortillas in bottom of dish, 1/2 meat mixture, 1 can beans, 1/2 soup mixture and diced cheese.
Make another layer in the same order until all ingredients are used.
End with 2 tortillas on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until real hot.

title: low calorie banana milk shake
directions: Put milk in blender.
Add vanilla and frozen bananas a little at a time.
If a thicker shake is desired, add ice cubes until desired thickness.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 8 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle rice over bottom of greased baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup, celery soup and milk in saucepan.
Heat on medium heat until soup mixture is heated through.
Do not boil.
Pour over rice. Stir.
Lay pieces of chicken over rice mixture, skin side up. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken pieces.
Cover baking dish tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, margarine and water to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with a mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
On a floured board, knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 equal pieces.
Shape into balls. Place in greased 8-inch round pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creamy pepper dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve with salad greens.
Yield:
1 cup (11 calories and 8% fat per tablespoon).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Freeze on wax paper on cookie sheet. Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin.
With toothpicks, dip frozen candy balls into chocolate. Makes 125 balls.

title: pasta and peas
directions: In a small saucepan, place oil and 2 cloves of garlic on medium heat.
Wait for garlic to brown slightly and then add can of tomato sauce and can of peas.
Cook until peas are soft (approximately 30 minutes).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to boil; stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla; mix in powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Spread in buttered 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm; cut into squares. Yields 3 1/2 pounds.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and slice lengthwise.
Place yolks in small mixing bowl.
Mash with fork; add mustard, relish, Miracle Whip and sugar.
Mix well.
Spoon into egg white halves and garnish with paprika.

title: aunt myrtle's cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar and butter.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
Drop on lightly greased pans. Bake about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease sides of pan.
Layer graham cracker and butter on bottom.
Mix well the cream cheese, lemon juice, egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla and pour over graham crackers. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Remove and cool for 10 - 15 minutes. Mix together sour cream, remaining sugar and vanilla. Pour on top of cheesecake and return to 450° oven.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: quick soup
directions: Brown ground beef in 2 to 3-quart pot.
Add instant onion and all other ingredients.
Cook
until potatoes are tender.

title: easy cheesy sauce(makes 8 tablespoons; 23 calories per tablespoon)
directions: In small saucepan, combine ingredients.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until Lite-line slices melt.
Serve warm over steamed vegetables, pasta, baked potato or broiled fish. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well. Cool.

(Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.) Combine mayonnaise or salad dressing and mustard in large bowl. Add cooled elbow macaroni, ham, onion, celery, relish, salt and pepper; toss lightly until well blended.
Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Add pie filling and bring to boil.
Add jello powder and stir until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple, lemon juice, nuts and Coke.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: alice springs chicken from outback steakhouse
directions: Use an electric mixer to combine the mustard, honey, 1 1/2 teaspoons (7 ml) oil and lemon juice in a small bowl.
Whip the mixture for about 30 seconds.
Pour about 2/3 of the marinade over the chicken breasts and marinate them, covered, in the refrigerator for about 2 hours.
Chill the remaining marinade until later.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Combine fruits and applesauce and arrange in a casserole.
Add cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Add juice of lemon (and rind).
Mix fruits and cover.
Bake at 250°
for at least 1 hour.
The longer it bakes the better it is.

title: meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and cracker crumbs and set aside. Add jelly and chili sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Quick, different and delicious.

title: old-fashioned butter cake
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition. Combine flour with baking soda and salt.
Add to batter alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on rack. Dust with powdered sugar before serving.

title: red punch
directions: Dissolve jello and Kool-Aid in 2 quarts of water.
Add pineapple juice and sugar.
Chill well.
When ready to serve, put first mixture in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale in and spoon in pineapple sherbet.
Makes approximately 12 servings.
May substitute raspberry or cherry jello and Kool-Aid.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Whisk flour, sugar and baking powder in large bowl to blend.
Using fingertips, rub 3/4 cup chilled butter into dry ingredients until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and stir until evenly moistened.
Using 1/4 cup dough for each biscuit, drop biscuits onto baking sheet, spacing 2-inches apart.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown on top, about 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, water and onion and put in little balls.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half and pat dry with cloth or paper towels.
In a large bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and coat each piece well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Arrange in single layer in baking dish. Melt margarine and spoon half over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes. Turn chicken and spoon on rest of margarine.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes until brown and tender.

title: pizza subs
directions: Cut lengthwise triangular shape from middle of each roll. Remove.
Spread spaghetti sauce on each roll, layer with pepperoni slices and cheese.
Add another layer of sauce, replace top of bun. Place in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: christmas scent
directions: Combine in a tea kettle or saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer as long as you want to.
Add more water, if needed.
Can be stored in icebox and reused.
This will make your whole house smell good.
You can also set it on a wood heater in a pot, and it will simmer as long as the heater is warm.
This is not to eat.
It is a room scenter.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water and put 1/4 cup aside for later use.
Mix large amount of jello with bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Place in refrigerator and let set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Stir together shredded zucchini, eggs oil and sugar. Stir together dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Put chicken breast in baking dish. Season with cajun spice, garlic salt, Johnny Seasoning Salt to taste. Bake at 350 for half an hour. Pour two packages of broccoli over the chicken and sprinkle with Cajun spice and four cups of Pepper Jack cheese over the broccoli and bake for half an hour to 45 minutes. Make sure the broccoli is done.

title: easy pecan pie(servings:  8)
directions: In medium saucepan, combine honey and butter; heat until boiling.
Set aside to cool.
When cooled, add pecans and beaten eggs.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour carrots
directions: Slice
carrots	and
steam
10	to
15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Mix
soup,
sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard and catsup in a
pan
and
heat until thickened (10 to 15 minutes).
Add remaining
ingredients
to	carrots.
Pour	soup
mixture over vegetables and mix together.
Chill several hours in a tightly covered container.	This will keep 1 to 2 weeks in fridge.

title: 1 2 3 pudding and sauce(sauce is optional)
directions: Combine soft shortening, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder very well. Add milk alternately with flour to shortening mixture; beat about 2 minutes.
Bake in a well-greased pan until done. We used a large skillet. Cooks or bakes a lovely pudding in about 40 or 45 minutes at approximately 325°.
Don't forget vanilla flavoring.

title: grammie's dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Adjust to taste.
May be used on either lettuce or cabbage salad.

title: clam roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In food processor or blender, place clams, cream cheese, catsup, parsley and horseradish.
Process 1 to 2 minutes, till blended.
Unroll crescent roll dough onto lightly floured surface.
Separate into 4 rectangles.
Spread each with 1/4 of clam mixture.
Roll each up tightly starting at a narrow end.
Cut each roll into 6 slices. Place cut side down on cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes, till lightly browned.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: coleslaw
directions: To cabbage add salt.
Let stand one hour or longer at room temperature.
Then squeeze or press out the liquid with hands. Just grab a handful and squeeze until all cabbage has been pressed.

title: cranberry frozen salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayo and sugar; add whole berry cranberry sauce and drained pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and whipped topping.
Put into mold or loaf pans and freeze.
Remove from pan and let soften a few minutes before serving.
Slice to serve.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Prick the potatoes.
Microwave on High until done.
Fry the bacon.
Remove from pan.
Fry pepper and onion in the bacon grease until tender and slightly brown.

title: microwave sweet corn
directions: Place sweet corn, leaving husks on, in microwave.
Microwave 3 1/2 minutes per ear.
Remove from microwave.
Husk and serve.

title: party mix
directions: Toss; let set at least 4 to 8 hours.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight jar.
To serve, add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of boiling water.

title: elvira's potato pot
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and grate.
Then mix all together.
Place in casserole.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lebanese tabouli
directions: Wash parsley in water as you would spinach, remove stems and drain well.
Roll handful of parsley into lettuce leaf, then squee-ee-eeze as much water out of it as possible.
Shred with scissors or sharp knife.
Shred all the lettuce and parsley in this way, building up a small mountain of greens in a large bowl or nonmetal pan.
The squeezing process is very necessary or resulting salad will be too watery.
Squeeze lemons and strain juice into glass container.
Do not use metal.
Wash bulghur and soak it in 2 or 3 cups of water for half an hour.
Mince scallions or onions and add to the greens.
Chop mint leaves, bruising them in your hands as you add them to greens.
Drain bulghur and add to the bowl.
Dice tomatoes (you need not peel them) and add to salad on top of bulghur so the juice will soak in.
Add lemon juice and drizzle olive oil over all.
Sprinkle salt on it, grind pepper happily over it and mix gently with your hands.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook beef in butter until crumbly. Add garlic salt, pepper and tomato sauce. Cook over low heat for 15 minutes. Cook noodles and drain. Chop onions and mix with cream cheese and sour cream. Alternate layers of noodles, cheese mixture and meat sauce in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese. Bake until cheese is bubbly at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add juice and beaten egg, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Pour over crushed pineapple, marshmallows and chopped peanuts.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Heat 1/2 cup water and add sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves; cool.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Serve with crushed ice.
Yields 24 servings.

title: southwest beef empanadas
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease cookie sheet. Cook beef in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, stirring, until brown. Drain. Stir in taco seasoning mix, 2/3 cup water, potatoes, carrots and onion. Heat beef mixture over medium heat 5 minutes. Stir Bisquick and boiling water until dough forms. Place dough on surface sprinkled with Bisquick. Roll in mix to coat. Knead 20 times. Divide dough into 6 balls. Pat or roll each ball into 7-inch circle. Place on cookie sheet. Spoon about 1/2 cup beef mixture onto half of each circle. Moisten edges and fold over, pressing edge with fork to seal. Make 3 small slits in each crust to allow steam to escape. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light brown. Serves 6.

title: salmon and wild rice soup
directions: Cook bacon in 3-quart pan until crisp.
Drain, reserving fat in saucepan.
Cook and stir onion, celery and mushrooms in fat until celery is tender.
Stir in flour, rosemary and mustard.

title: cherry fudge cake
directions: Combine all and mix well with spoon (no mixer).
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: steamed spareribs with black beans
directions: Mix
all ingredients together with spareribs; let stand for 20	minutes
or
more.
Steam
for	35
minutes
or more. Garnish with 1 stalk green onion (finely chopped) and Chinese parsley. Serve hot.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Add all at one time to large frying pan and cook slowly until meat
is cooked.
Then add 6 ground
up
wieners.
Cook until heated through.
Serve on hot dogs.
Serve	with chopped sweet onions and mustard.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle sausage over bread, then add cheese and mushrooms.
Beat together eggs, mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk and pour over top of mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours. Combine soup and 1/2 cup milk when ready to bake and pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: potatoes and hamburger meat loaf
directions: Arrange the first 5 ingredients in greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix the rest of ingredients and spread over potatoes.
Put ketchup on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix cornmeal, baking powder and garlic salt.
Add eggs, corn and oil.
Stir well.
Then add peppers and cheese.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana slush
directions: In a large saucepan boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Cool. In large nonmetal container combine bananas, juices and sugar; mix.
Freeze.
Two hours before serving, remove mixture from freezer.
Before serving, stir in 7-Up.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate. Use for dip for any fresh vegetable.

title: lucia bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons lukewarm milk.
Mix with sugar, flour, egg and 2 tablespoons milk to make dough.
Cover; place in warm spot to rise 15 minutes.
Put saffron into bowl with 4 tablespoons milk.
Add salt.
Melt, but do not heat butter.
Pour over saffron mixture.
Add mixture to risen dough.
Knead thoroughly until dough does not stick to bowl.
Cover and place in warm spot to rest 30 minutes.
If necessary or desired, knead and let rise again.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Place pork chops into baking dish.
Place on top of each chop: onion, lemon, brown sugar and catsup.
Cover with foil and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and finish cooking for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Pour onion soup mix over meat.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover and cook 1 to 2 hours or until tender.
Add water as needed.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch mixed in 1/2 cup cold water.
Good with noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash collard greens and cut into large pieces.
Put water in large pot and add salt pork meat.
Let water and meat come to a boil.
Add cut collard greens.
When greens become tender, add hot pepper to taste.

title: sausage and cheese crescent squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Unroll 1 can of dough into 2 long rectangles. Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish; press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides to form crust. Brown sausage in large skillet over medium heat until thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently. Remove sausage from skillet; discard drippings. Add cream cheese to same skillet. Cook over low heat until melted. Add cooked sausage; stir to coat. Spoon evenly over crust in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Unroll second can of dough on work surface. Press to form 13 x 9-inch rectangle; firmly press perforations to seal. Place over cheese. Bake at 375° for 21 to 26 minutes or until brown. Cool 15 minutes. Cut into small squares.

title: pea salad
directions: Heat first five ingredients to boiling.
Set aside to cool. Mix all the vegetables together.
Pour the vinegar mixture over the vegetables.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: easter egg cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Put 1/4 in bowl and color deep yellow.
Use 1 level teaspoonful and roll in balls.
Freeze.
Divide 3/4 of dough into 3 parts and tint pink, green, etc.
Take one level teaspoonful.
Shape around yellow balls.
Refrigerate.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets 1 inch apart. Do not brown too much.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: In large bowl, with electric mixer on medium, beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour until smooth and well combined.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Divide dough into two parts and refrigerate for several hours.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
On lightly floured surface, roll out one part at a time to 1/3 inch thickness.
Using any shape cookie cutters, cut out cookies.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake cookies for 25 minutes or until light golden.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: corn bread mexican style
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients.
Set aside.
Saute meat in skillet.
Drain; add 1/2 cup water and cook until no longer red. In a 10 x 10-inch baking pan, put in half the corn bread mixture. Put a layer of meat mixture on top of this.
Add rest of corn bread mixture and top with a cup of cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until done.
Don't overcook, but needs to be well done.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Combine cream cheese, chiles, nuts, olives and garlic powder. Completely cover one side of tortilla with above mixture.
Roll up each tortilla tightly jelly roll style.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
To serve, cut each roll into 1/2-inch rounds and lay cut side down on serving tray.

title: fresh fruit shell salad
directions: Prepare shells as package directs; drain.
In small bowl, blend yogurt and orange juice concentrate.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add yogurt mixture; toss to coat.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 10 servings.

title: autumn apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat oil, margarine and sugar together. Add the eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Use an electric mixer.

Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon and soda; stir into batter. Add all the remaining ingredients and stir to blend. Turn the mixture into a 9-inch angel food tube pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan before turning out.
Serve at room temperature with rich vanilla ice cream.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add vinegar and lemon juice. Add oil slowly while beating with mixer until thickens. Great for fresh fruit salad.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: This is one of the most popular Italian chicken dishes.
Put 1/2 of the olive oil in a large casserole over low heat and cook onions until soft.
Roll chicken pieces in flour, salt and pepper. Skim out onions and reserve.
Add remaining oil to casserole. Brown chicken and return onions.
Add tomatoes, pepper, garlic and herbs.
Cover closely and simmer over low heat, about 1 hour, or until chicken is very tender.

title: creamy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place potatoes and onion in 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with pork chops, salt and pepper if desired.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger with brown gravy
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add the brown gravy mix, following the directions on back of package, then add the Worcestershire sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf with carrots
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Cool.
Mix beef, onion, oats, ketchup, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Spread 1/2 mixture in pan.
Put carrots on mixture and cover with rest of meat mixture.
Put bacon on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Turn bacon and bake 30 more minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a small bowl, combine honey, salt, vinegar and mustard. Gradually add oil, beating thoroughly until mixture is well blended.
Stir in poppy seed.
Place in a pint jar, cover and chill several hours before serving.
Shake well before using. Serve over fruit salad.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and lemon juice together well.
Stir cream cheese mixture and other ingredients together.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: In saucepan, cook carrots until tender.
Add peppers; cook slightly.
Drain pineapple.
Keep juice.
Add water to juice to make 1/3 cup liquid.
Remove carrots and peppers.
Discard water. In pan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in pineapple liquid, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook until bubbly.
Add vegetables and pineapple.

title: chocolate peanut butter sandwich snacks
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave or stove according to package instructions.
Using approximately 1 teaspoon of peanut butter, make sandwiches, using 2 Ritz crackers.
Dip sandwich in chocolate, covering completely.
Lay on wax paper until firm.
Can be stored in refrigerator.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir until thawed.
Add sliced bananas and chopped pecans.
Pour mixture into 8
x 8 x 12-inch pan and refrigerate until firm. Spread sour cream on top.

title: english pub mustard
directions: Mix dry ingredients in blender.
Slowly add beer and blend until smooth.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Makes about 2 cups.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix together, heat and thicken with 1 tablespoon flour, stirring until thick.
Serve
with	Smok-Y-Links, hamburger or ham.

title: sausage and cheese balls(singal bash)
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Mix everything together.
Make balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: pow!
directions: Heat all ingredients to simmering, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with celery "swizzle sticks".
Makes 6 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: easy no-roll sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter with sugar and egg until very light and fluffy.
Sift flour with salt, baking soda and cream of tartar right into bowl.
Beat at low speed until well combined; beat in vanilla.

title: pineapple sandwich filling
directions: Cook eggs, flour, sugar and juice from pineapple until thick, then add pineapple.
Spread bread with mayonnaise and add filling.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together.
Pat mixture into long cake pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator well.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix gelatin, cake mix, eggs, water and oil. Pour into 9-inch round cake pans that have been buttered and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: alabama hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with enough milk to make mixture paste-like.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot grease.
Yields 12 servings.

title: crunchy chews
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in peanut butter; add cereal, stirring to coat evenly.
Pour into a square greased pan or spoon out.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, eggs, brown sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Then stir in corn syrup until blended, making as little foam as possible.
Fold in pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 375° until filling is set.
Cool slightly.
Great with vanilla ice cream.

title: lemon buttermilk chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine sugar, cornmeal, flour and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar mixture; mix well.
Add melted butter, lemon zest and juice, buttermilk and vanilla to egg mixture, mixing to blend thoroughly after each addition to prevent lumping.
Pour the mixture into the unbaked pie shell; bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until the top is golden brown and custard is set.
Remove pie to rack; cool completely.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar and garnish each serving with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: plain cake
directions: Use as a basic cake for many toppings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar; mix.
Add flour; mix.
Add milk. Cook until thick.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla, butter and coconut.
Pour in baked pie crusts.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Spread on pie.
Bake 400° until golden brown.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in large bowl.
Spread cheese, Miracle Whip and sugar over salad.
Let stand 24 hours.
Stir just before serving.

title: chicken with mushrooms and rice
directions: * May substitute 1/2 cup dry white wine for 1/2 cup of the water.

title: lonu lomi salmon
directions: Shred salmon.
Combine salmon, tomatoes, green onions, onion and water.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Add ice before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Combine shortening and water in a saucepan on medium heat.
Add flour when mixture begins to boil. Switch heat to low.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth and mixture forms a smooth mass.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in margarine over medium heat.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder and mushrooms. Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Add soup, simmer uncovered 10 more minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: punch
directions: Let ice cream unthaw for 1/2 hour.
Then blend well.

title: shoyu chicken--hawaiian style
directions: Combine sugar, water, soy sauce, pineapple juice, oil, ginger and garlic powder.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over chicken wings in bowl small enough so that all are covered.
Cover and refrigerate.
Marinate at least one full day (two is preferable), stirring occasionally.

title: boiled potato salad
directions: Mix together in saucepan flour, sugar, dry mustard, salt, cider vinegar and water over medium high heat.
Cool until thick and bubbly.
Add butter.
Pour hot over cooked, cut up eggs, potatoes and onions.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight.

title: pilgrim's progress punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve in punch bowl.
This is a beary tasty punch, not too tart, not too sweet.

title: lemon squares
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat butter for 30 seconds; add the 1/4 cup of sugar and 1/4 cup flour.
Pat dough onto bottom of pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in vanilla, flour and nuts. Chill.
Shape into balls, approximately the size of a hickory nut. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy day casserole(slow cooker)
directions: Mix meat, soup mix, wine and mushroom soup.
Squeeze lemon juice over and mix well. Cook on low setting all day in slow cooker.
Near end of cooking time, add the frozen vegetables.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Combine butter and cheese.
Stir in sugar, vanilla and cocoa. Press in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and cool until firm.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve on a beautifully decorated platter.

title: microwave potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes and water in a 2-quart glass casserole dish; cover.
Microwave on High for 8 to 12 minutes, or until tender, stirring after 6 minutes.
Drain; stir in remaining ingredients. Mix lightly.
Chill.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping as the package directs.
Combine 1 cup of prepared topping with pudding mix, pumpkin, milk and spices. Mix slowly with electric mixer just until blended, about 1 minute. Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill until set, at least 2 hours. Garnish with remaining whipped topping.

title: venison patties
directions: Catch a deer, then grind venison and chopped bacon.
Put in balance of ingredients; mix by hand.
Form into 3-inch diameter roll.
Cut into slices and fry.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Rub chicken breasts with lemon, salt, pepper and flour. Saute in butter for 7 minutes on each side. Remove from heat and put chicken in baking pan dish. Mix together remaining ingredients. Deglaze the saute pan, scraping in all the ingredients. Strain the sauce over the chicken breasts. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top and brown lightly under the broiler for a few minutes.

title: cheese wafers with rice krispies
directions: Melt margarine and add cheese, salt, sugar and pepper; blend well.

title: five pounds of wonderful fudge
directions: Combine butter, canned milk and sugar in a large heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook to a boil; cover and boil 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add 3 kinds of chocolate, one at a time, stirring until melted.
Add vanilla extract and nuts; blend.
Pour into buttered pan (jelly roll), 10 x 15-inch, and let stand until firm before cutting in 1-inch squares.
Whole pecan halves can be pressed into tops of squares if you wish!

title: honey mix
directions: Bring margarine, honey, and brown sugar to a boil for 5 minutes, without stirring.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
While mixture is coming to a boil, spray a roasting pan with Pam.
Put in cereal, nuts, and pretzels.
Pour the glaze over when ready and stir.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool on cookie sheets.
Break up and store in airtight container.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place large berries in pie shell.
Crush remaining berries. Add sugar and cornstarch; cook until thick.
When cool, pour over berries in shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: rainbow wedges
directions: Cut oranges in half.
Remove the pulp.
Fix Jell-O according to package directions.
Fill the orange halves with the Jell-O. Chill, cut halves in quarters.
Can also be done with cantaloupe.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Mix flour, salt and soda;
add
to
batter.
Add
chips
and nuts. Shape into balls.
Drop on
cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Blend together for several minutes.
Pour into two pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Melt oleo, then combine with other ingredients.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Bake another 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into patties and barbecue over hot coals.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Crush up all but a few pecans.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on the box, add powdered sugar, cream cheese and crushed pecans.
Mix with mixer on low until blended well.
Pour this mixture over graham cracker crust.
Pour cherry pie filling on top, then decorate the top with a few whole pecans.

title: cherry mousse
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients and stir.
Cover and refrigerate or serve immediately.

title: zucchini
directions: Scoop pulp from zucchini, leaving 1/4-inch in shells.
Cut pulp in pieces and mixed with remaining ingredients.
Spoon about 3 tablespoons into each shell.
Microwave for 6 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and vanilla in microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir.
Add confectioners sugar.
Mix very well.
Mold in rectangular pan.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: mom's lemon pie
directions: Use double boiler.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add water; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cover and place over boiling water 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add a little hot mixture; stir.
Pour back.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, butter and grated peel.
Cool at room temperature; do not stir.
Pour into cooled, baked pastry shell.

title: rae's pickles
directions: Fill 1 gallon glass jar with cukes (whole, maybe large ones). Add 4 tablespoons pickling spice and remaining ingredients.

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove bones and chop.
Cook onion, green pepper and celery in chicken broth until tender.
Add spaghetti.
Cook until tender.
Add soup and pimentos.

title: milk chocolate cake
directions: Mix in order of ingredients.
Bake in 2 layers at 375°.
Frost with 7 Minute Icing.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: You can leave out the oats or any one of the last six ingredients if you don't like one.
Mix all together in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart. Bake at 325° until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Put in bread pan. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; set aside 1 cup of nuts.
Put bowl in refrigerator until chilled and slightly firm.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Keep chilled until ready to use.

title: chicken, red grape and apple salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes, apples, celery, raisins and onions in a bowl; toss gently.
Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, lemon juice and celery leaves in a bowl; stir well.
Add to chicken mixture; toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill.
Serve on individual lettuce-lined serving plates.
Yield:
6 servings; serving size:
1 cup, 183 calories per serving.
Recipe is from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: aurora salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding the oranges last.
Excellent served with ham.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Line bottom and sides of baking dish with wafers.
Combine pudding mix, milk and butter in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Layer banana slices then pour on half the pudding.
Repeat layers.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: sweet 'n low cake
directions: Beat together salad oil, Sweet 'N Low, eggs and buttermilk. Sift
together
flour,
nutmeg, cinnamon and soda.	Add liquid ingredients.
Add
diced
prunes (or apples) and nuts. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to jello and stir to dissolve.
Wash cranberries and run through food grinder.
Add orange juice, pineapple with its juices, sugar and pecans to cranberries.
When gelatin has cooled, combine all ingredient and refrigerate.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Layer ice cream sandwiches and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts.
Make a second layer. In a pot, mix 1 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons chocolate and 1/4 cup milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 stick of butter or margarine. Spoon this over top of Cool Whip.
Cover and freeze overnight.

title: brownie delight
directions: Bake brownies according to directions (this is a double batch).
Before baking brownies, sprinkle walnuts, pecans and chocolate chips, approximately 1/2 cup of each (or to your liking).
When done, let cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *You may also use spinach or cauliflower or a combination of vegetables (broccoli and cauliflower).

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, Blue cheese and pepper; form into a ball and roll in walnuts.
May be served with crackers, fruit and pretzels.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare loaf pan.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add one egg and beat well; then add 2nd egg and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and banana.
Mix well.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes.

title: salsa de tomatillo
directions: Boil chiles, tomatoes and tomatillos for about 20 minutes. Blend the garlic cloves, salt and 1 cup of water from the tomatillos and chiles.
Blend it for about 3 minutes, then pour into a bowl and let it cool down.
Then mix the 2 chopped avocados and mix it and it's ready to serve.

title: ambberg trout
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, mustard and milk in a large bowl.
In separate bowl, combine corn meal and seasoned salt.
Heat oil to boiling.
Baste trout in milk mixture, then roll in corn meal mixture.
Be sure to get all cavities.
Fry until golden.
Drain well on paper towels; remove as much oil as possible.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into shallow greased pan (8 x 8-inch).
Cover with sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: no cook cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and salt; bring to a rapid boil. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper (work quickly).
Makes 40 to 45 cookies.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in pecans.
Press mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream margarine and cheese and add flour, then cereal.
Roll into small, marble-sized balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork, which has been dipped in flour.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt while hot.
Store in airtight container or freeze.

title: no cook candy
directions: Add all ingredients in saucepan.
Stir slowly over heat until peanut butter is melted.
Spread onto buttered dish.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion.
Mix sugar, vinegar and seasonings. Heat 4 minutes.
Put cucumbers and onion in; cook for 8 minutes. Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (on bun).

title: walnut duxelles
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter with green onions and thyme.
Add salt and sherry. Cook until liquid has almost evaporated, about 8 minutes.
Let cool a little. Add cream cheese, walnuts and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well. Chill overnight, covered. Garnish with parsley. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: mozzarella shell salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salad is best served the same day.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box (11 x 13-inch pan). Let cool.
Make pudding, using 1/4 cup Amaretto for some of the milk.
Layer in trifle bowl, 1/2 cake (crumbled), 1/2 pudding, 1/2 crushed Heath bar and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat; chill and garnish with almonds.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Whip the whipping cream until stiff.
Sweeten with sugar to taste.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: penuche frosted banana cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt in medium bowl and set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugar and 1/2 cup margarine.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
Continue beating 1 minute.
Continue beating, gradually adding flour mixture, for 1 minute.
By hand, stir in 1/2 cup walnuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: sticky bun cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter, water and cinnamon; put them in the baking pan.
Microwave mixture on High until butter is melted, about 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Put all the pieces into the pan.
Stir gently with spatula to coat all the pieces with sugar mixture.
Spread pieces into an even layer, then microwave cake on High for 5 minutes. Remove from oven.
If it's still doughy, cook longer until done.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Drain water off of cherries.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour; mix well with cherries, then add lemon juice and butter.
Mix well.
Butter 1 medium-sized Pyrex dish, then pour 1/2 of mixture in dish.

title: lasagne
directions: Add olive oil and 1 tablespoon salt to rapidly boiling water. Gradually add lasagne noodles so that water continues to boil. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender and drain. Mix Ricotta, eggs, salt, pepper, parsley and Parmesan together. Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 1/3 meat sauce. Place 1/3 Mozzarella over sauce and top with Ricotta mixture.
Add a layer of 1/2 the lasagne.
Repeat layers.
Cover with remaining meat sauce and cheeses.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: t's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball.
Roll in pecan pieces.

title: beans supreme
directions: Brown ground beef in a heavy skillet; add onions, green peppers and mushrooms.
Cook until vegetables are lightly browned.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, soup, beans and salt.
Put in a 3-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Great for parties.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and margarine; spread over peanut butter layer.
Chill.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all together; place in large casserole dish with tight fitting lid.
Bake at 250° for 6 to 12 hours.
Great served over noodles.

title: pasta with an uncommon sauce
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion in oil, over medium heat, 5 minutes, or until translucent.
Set aside.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Place a small amount of chicken on the wide end of each one and roll up.
Seal and place sealed side down in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Thoroughly combine the soup and milk.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no-bake peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine.
Boil mixture 1 1/2 minutes, then add oats and peanut butter.
Stir thoroughly and drop by teaspoons on wax paper and allow to set until cold.
Press down flat with a fork if desired.

title: bath tub mixture(hot cocoa)
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large container (bath tub). Store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup mixture to 1 cup hot water for instant hot cocoa.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, corn, sugar and egg.
Add buttermilk slowly (enough to mix to drop from spoon).
Drop in hot oil and brown.
Great with fish and onion.
Serve hot and quick meal if in hurry.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Whip eggs until they foam.
Add flour, sugar and pudding. Beat mixture.
Add 1/2 gallon of milk.
Cook until piping hot. Remove from heat and add the remaining milk.
Cool, then add flavoring.
(You can use flavoring of your choice such as lemon, almond, etc.)

title: terrificly tender pot roast
directions: Place roast in pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Slice onion and separate rings.
Add rings to roast.
Cover.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Peel and halve potatoes.
Peel carrots, cut lengthwise and cut in half.
Cut celery lengthwise and cut in half.
Add to roast.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Mix together meal, celery, onion, egg and buttermilk.
Mix like cornbread and bake.
Cool and crumble in large bowl.
Add chicken, chicken soup, salt, pepper, sage and chicken broth.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm.

title: aunt betty's famous lasagna and sausage
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed, cool.
Wrap cheese around sausages, then wrap lasagna noodles around sausages.
Place in an uncovered baking dish and pour Prego sauce over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Add lemon juice to egg yolks with milk.
Make graham cracker crust for filling.
Pour egg filling in shell.
Beat egg whites for icing with dash of sugar.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: deviled ham balls
directions: Have cheese at room temperature; cream with ham.
Put in refrigerator until cool enough to shape into balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Place toothpick in each ball when ready to serve.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in tube pan or 2 loaf pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: coconut crumb cherry pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add coconut and stir until mixture is crumbly.
Set aside.
Bake pastry shell at 450° for 5 minutes.
Cook pie filling over medium heat just until hot.
Pour in shell.
Sprinkle coconut mixture over filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: quick cookies(chocolate)
directions: Put first 4 items in heavy pan; bring to hard boil, stirring. Take from stove and put in oatmeal and coconut.
Put on wax paper in spoonful mounds to cool.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour.
Add salt, coconut, nuts and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a preheated 275° oven.
Store cooled cookies in air-tight container about 5 days before serving.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream all wet ingredients.
Add all the dry.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place in tea size papers into teacup tins.
Bake until lightly browned.
As soon as you remove from the oven, press the butter cups in the center of papers with cookies.
Cool before removing from the pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake in small shaped loaves in Pyrex pan about 350° until thoroughly cooked.

title: tuna appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add chocolate syrup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Leave in pan.

title: pasta with peas, prosciutto and parmesan
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add onions and saute over low heat 5 minutes.
Stir in cream, basil and Prosciutto.
Cook until thickened to a good coating consistency 15 minutes.
Add peas; cook 3 to 4 minutes or just until peas turn bright green.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat and stir in Parmesan cheese.
Pour over hot drained pasta and toss gently.

title: infallible onion rice
directions: Saute onion until transparent in the margarine.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add raw white rice and hot broth; stir.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Place in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: empanadas(mexican cookies)
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and flour together.
Cut flour in with a fork.
Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness, using a floured rolling pin.
Use mouth of a 16-ounce drinking cup to cut circles in dough.
Place 1/2 to 1 tablespoon jelly preserves in center of each circle.
Fold in half and seal edges with a fork.

title: roulade
directions: Pound steak and cut into 3 x 5-inch pieces.
Fry bacon with 2 cups onions and parsley.
Sprinkle 1 side of meat with salt and pepper; spread bacon on the meat.
Roll meat tightly and tie or secure with toothpick.
Coat with flour.
Heat oleo in casserole dish with lid.
When hot, brown meat lightly and remove.
Add 1 onion and carrot and brown slowly, about 5 to 7 minutes, stirring several times, until golden brown.
Place meat rolls on top and add water and tomato puree.
Cover; bring to boil and reduce heat and simmer slowly 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: carrot salad
directions: Place carrots in food processor and grind fine. Soak raisins in hot water for a few minutes. Rinse and add to carrots. Add Sweet 'N Low and mayonnaise to taste.

title: veal roll-ups
directions: Place one slice of ham and Swiss cheese on each piece of veal steak.
Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end.
Secure rolls with toothpicks.
Mix flour and seasonings.
Dust veal with seasoned flour.
Dip floured rolls into beaten egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Brown in hot shortening.
Pour wine over meat. Cover and simmer for 55 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve with pasta or rice.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash the broccoli and cauliflower.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Coarsely chop boiled eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: easy-camper-skillet dish
directions: Lightly brown sausage and remove from skillet.
Add cabbage, potatoes and onion.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle on the flour and mix well.
Add water to broth to make 1 1/2 cups broth.
Put sausage back in, add broth, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with can of cherry pie filling.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar and curry powder and dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: melon delight
directions: Refrigerate all ingredients overnight.
The next day, scoop balls or pieces from melons.
Clean grapes and hull strawberries. Cut the watermelon in half (lengthwise) in either a straight cut or a "zigzag" edge.
Save the top half for later use.
Hollow out the watermelon for a "bowl."
Make more balls from the melon also.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Coarsely
chop
tomatoes,
onions,
celery, cabbage and pepper. Cover with
cup salt; let stand for 2 hours. Drain. Then add rest
of ingredients. Boil slowly for 1 hour. Seal in jars.
Makes 10 pints.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, vanilla, corn syrup, cream, eggs, salt and cinnamon and mix well.
Add pecans and pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: maple fudge
directions: Put syrup and cream in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil on high heat.
Continue cooking on medium heat to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm; beat until thick and gloss has disappeared. Add nuts and pour into greased pan.
Cut in squares.

title: fig bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and figs.
Add flavoring.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° in 2 greased pans for 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine this and freeze in electric ice cream freezer.
One serving equals two cups.

title: cranberry-yams casserole
directions: Combine the oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Mix all but 1 cup of the crumb mixture with the cranberries and yams.
(The leftover goes on top.)
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 35 minutes, then add the mini marshmallows and broil until browned.

title: sunday beef roast
directions: Put frozen roast in crock-pot on low on Saturday night (10 to 11 p.m.).
Cook on low until morning.
Turn roast over and spread the can of soup (undiluted) over roast.
Cook on low until after a.m. church.
Very tender and very easy.

title: taco rice casserole
directions: Crumble and cook hamburger; drain off excess fat.
Add taco seasoning and salt.
Cook for a few minutes; then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Layer in casserole with slices of American cheese.
Bake long enough for cheese to melt.

title: pinkie's cheese ball
directions: Roll in ball or mound up in glob.

title: pour man's pudding
directions: Beat eggs. Add all other ingredients in saucepan; heat on medium until hot. Add leftover homemade biscuits, torn into pieces. Stir and serve warm.

title: ham balls
directions: In a bowl, combine the pork, ham, eggs, milk and cereal; mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2 in. to 2 in. balls; place in a greased 13 in. x 9 in. x 2 in. baking dish.

title: vegetable pizza(appetizer)
directions: Mix cream cheese, Ranch mix and mayonnaise and save for later. Cook crust at temperature stated on package until lightly browned.
When crust is cool, spread cream cheese mixture evenly on crust and top with the assorted vegetables.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: italian salad regis
directions: Shake oil and vinegar together.
Put all other ingredients, except
Romano cheese and tomatoes, in a salad bowl and toss gently.
Sprinkle
oil
and vinegar over salad.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat all ingredients except Cool Whip until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust; top with grated chocolate bar or cookie crumbs. Refrigerate before serving.

title: polish noodles
directions: Brown in skillet 10 strips bacon, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Add water and sugar to browned bacon.
Now add cabbage, cut up into pieces.
Do not use core.
Cook slowly.
Cook noodles as directed. Drain; put into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add bacon and cabbage mixture; stir.
Add sour cream.
Stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste, cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
M-M-M-M good!

title: tangy sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl, scraping the sides often.
Take 1 teaspoon of the cookie dough and roll it into a ball.
Dip the ball into a bowl of sugar; thoroughly cover the dough.
Place cookies onto greased cookie sheets and flatten.
Bake for 7 minutes or until cookies are slightly golden.
Do not overbake.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: strawberry vanilla pudding
directions: Place angel food cake cubes in a 9 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Combine vanilla pudding and milk.
Add vanilla ice cream.
Mix, pour over cake cubes.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in boiling water; add frozen strawberry slices.
Stir until Jell-O thickens.
Pour over pudding and cake.
Do not stir.
Chill until set.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute vegetables in olive oil.
Add sausage and stir-fry for approximately 20 minutes or until brown.
Add raw rice, consomme and onion soup mix.
Stir well.
Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce to low heat.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.

title: mateo's chili especial
directions: The Extras:

Whatever else you can find in the fridge or pantry (old forgotten half-empty jars of Pace picante sauce, a dash or five of fajita seasoning, a squeeze of lime, beer, crushed red pepper, just whatever you can find).

title: "cheese and green chili burritos"
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stack the tortillas, wrap in foil and heat 5 to 10 minutes, until soft.
Sprinkle cheese, tomatoes, chilies and onions on half of each tortilla; fold other half over filling. Place on cookie sheet and bake 5 to 7 minutes.
Cut each tortilla in half and place on a platter.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Blend chips and milk in blender until smooth.
Add marshmallows and blend until smooth.

title: chickpea soup
directions: Remove sausage from casings.
Brown in frypan until cooked. Slice mushrooms lengthwise; add to sausage.
Put sausage and mushrooms in large pan and add water, tomato paste, onion and chickpeas.
Bring to a boil and simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and garlic in margarine and oil until tender. Stir in parsley, oregano, wine, clams with juice and mushrooms.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Serve over hot linguine.
Sprinkle with Romano. (Recipe can be doubled.)
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well together, then add 1/4 cup coconut and pour into uncooked pie shell. Cook until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients; reserve 1/3 cup chopped beef to roll ball in. Form mixture into ball.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients, except for pecans.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion; drain.
Cook noodles; drain.
Heat sauce and add to hamburger mix.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole, place hamburger mix, noodles and Cheddar cheese, grated.
Cover with grated Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° until melted.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs to mixture one at a time.
Add cake flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Place 3/4 of batter into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Cover filling with remaining batter.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, onions and 1/4 cup cheese. Reserve.
Stir in sauce, water, oil and powder.
Heat through. Place 2 rounded tablespoons chicken mixture on each tortilla. Roll up.
Place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Spoon remaining mixture over tortillas.
Pour tomato sauce over tortillas. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake until hot (15 to 20 minutes). Makes 4 servings.

title: fantastic fruit dip
directions: Cream together and serve in a small bowl with assorted fruit tray (bananas, strawberries, pineapple, apples, etc.).

title: spareribs(one dish; serves 4)
directions: Add ingredients; pour over ribs.
Bake ribs for 30 minutes at 450°, then bake for 45 minutes at 350°, basting with sauce every 10 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Slice potatoes. Cover with water in saucepan. Add onions and salt. Boil over medium heat until tender. Drain and place in a greased casserole dish. In a saucepan, melt margarine. Stir in flour, mustard and seasoned salt. When thick, add milk. Beat with whisk until thick. Add 2 cups cheese. Stir until melted. Pour this mixture over potatoes in casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs, cheese and paprika. Bake in a 300° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix the vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise very well and refrigerate overnight.
May substitute 1/2 cup mayonnaise with nonfat plain yogurt.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, beans and 1/2 can onion rings and bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and top with the other 1/2 can onion rings and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown (if using flour).

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add egg; beat until fluffy. Sift together the remaining dry ingredients.
Stir into molasses mixture.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Form into small balls; roll in sugar.
Place, 2 inches apart, on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Pull chicken off the bone and cut into bite-size pieces and place in bottom of long casserole dish. Mix stuffing mix, chicken broth and butter.
Spread over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over Cool Whip; mix well.
Add cottage cheese, oranges (chopped and drained) and pineapple (drained).
Mix well. Refrigerate about 3 hours before serving.

title: best ever sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Put aside to rise.
Scald milk.
Add sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs (beaten), melted butter, potatoes and yeast.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead slightly.
Let rise until double.
May roll for cinnamon rolls or cut for doughnuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: mauve punch
directions: Combine juices; carefully add soda.
Chill with ice.

title: quick pickled beets
directions: Reserve the liquid from beets and cook with sugar and vinegar. Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over beets and let set overnight.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix ingredients in order: Eagle Brand milk, chocolate syrup, evaporated milk, eggs and sugar.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm.
Makes 2 to 3 pies.

title: saturday cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° until cake is done.
Cut and serve with sweetened strawberries.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix the ingredients together thoroughly.
Add plain flour gradually and mix to consistency of biscuit dough.
Roll out on floured surface and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Keep in tight container.
Tea cakes will keep for weeks.

title: mexican layered sandwich
directions: Mix cooked drained ground beef with taco seasoning.
Place 1 tortilla on plate.
Top with lettuce, half of meat, and another tortilla.
Spread guacamole even over tortilla.
(Use sour cream if you don't like guacamole.)
Sprinkle with half of each: cheese, olives, pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with cilantro and top with another tortilla and meat.
Top with last tortilla.
Spread sour cream evenly on tortilla.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, olives, pepper and onions.
Top with reserved guacamole.
Serve immediately, or cover and refrigerate up to 3 hours.
Cut into wedges and serve with salsa.

title: fudgy cocoa brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a medium saucepan, melt shortening over low heat.
Remove melted shortening from heat; add cocoa.
Stir until well blended.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts.
Spread in prepared pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted is clean.

title: country cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Pour ingredients into a bowl and mix well by hand.
Put into greased 9 x 12-inch or larger pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Slice while warm. You can double this recipe for a bigger amount or larger pieces.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute over low heat onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Add soups, Picante sauce and enchilada mix.
Prepare your cooked chicken or turkey.
Use large or medium flour tortillas.
Spread a little of your sauce on tortilla; add some chopped up chicken or turkey and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Roll up.
Lay into pan that has been sprayed with Pam or slightly greased.
Pour enchilada sauce over all.

title: fajitas
directions: Saute sliced onion and peppers.
Debone the chicken.
Cut chicken and beef into strips.
Sprinkle fajita seasoning and let stand.
Grate the cheese and slice olives.
When vegetables are done, set aside and cook meat on medium.
When done, pour vegetables in meat.
Use flour tortillas and fill with cheese, sour cream, olives and fajita mix.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with mayonnaise.	Fold in remaining ingredients.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Add butter and milk.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Add biscuits that have been rolled out and cut into small pieces.
While adding biscuits, make sure there is a continuous boil to prevent dumplings from sticking.
Continue to boil until all dumplings are cooked throughout.

title: watermelon salad
directions: Cut large amount of watermelon and cantaloupe in bite size pieces or balls.
Add sliced bananas, bite size pineapple and seedless grapes (cut grapes in half if they are tart).
Clean out and notch half of watermelon rind.
Put mixture in rind and chill well.
Serve with Poppy Seed Dressing, Ritz or cheese crackers and salted nuts.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Dredge roast in flour and brown slightly in skillet.
Place roast in crock-pot; combine soups and seasonings.
Place potatoes around and on top of roast.
Pour soups over all.
Cook on low heat overnight or 8 to 10 hours.

title: tuna salad
directions: Add Miracle Whip mayonnaise to taste.
Chill.
Serve on bed of lettuce leaves.
Top with dill weed.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool slightly.
Heat pineapple (undrained) with 1/2 cup sugar until sugar is melted.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar in small mixing bowl.
You may need to mix 1 to 2 tablespoons of water for spreading consistency.
Spread cream cheese frosting on cake; refrigerate.

title: old fashioned blackberry cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar and milk; add water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in blackberries.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter and lightly sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Crumble tuna in bottom of buttered baking dish; smooth peas and carrots over tuna.
Smooth mushroom soup over peas and carrots.
Add water.
Cover top with crumbled potato chips.
Add butter.
Cook in 450° oven until juice begins to brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit pie
directions: Drain cherries and mix with crushed pineapple.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add to cherries and pineapple.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and add dry jello.
Let mixture cool in pan.
Add sliced bananas and nuts. Pour into pie shell and top with whipped cream.
Can be frozen up to 2 weeks.

title: apricot ham
directions: Remove skin and fat.
Place ham on rack in pan.
Combine mustard and jam; spread on ham.
Pat brown sugar over jam.
Insert cloves in diamond pattern.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325°.
Baste every 20 minutes.

title: grilled ham
directions: Mix all 4 top ingredients.
Brush onto ham or pork chops. Cook on grill (gas or charcoal).

title: fluffy 2-step easter cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk or electric mixer on high speed until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Spoon pie filling evenly over top of pie. Store leftover cheesecake in the refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses, then milk and dry ingredients.
Bake in 4 small layers in moderate oven (350°).

title: chicken elegant
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 40 minutes.

title: white christmas punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add evaporated milk and almond extract. Let cool. Chill until ready to serve.

title: chili
directions: Crumble ground beef into a slow cooker.
Add beans, onion, garlic and green pepper.
In a medium bowl, stir together tomatoes, tomato paste, water, chili powder, salt, oregano, cumin, pepper and cayenne pepper until well blended.
Stir into meat mixture.
Scrape down sides of slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or on low for 7 to 8 hours or until onion is tender.
Serve with shredded Cheddar and saltine crackers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: batter bread
directions: Cut margarine into the flour.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup very warm water.
Add yeast, egg and 1 1/2 cups very warm water to the flour all at once.
Beat until well blended.
Looks light and fluffy when you finish mixing it.
You can spoon it out immediately into well-greased muffin tins or you can use part of it now and store the rest in the refrigerator.
It can be stored for several days.
Fill muffins about 1/2 full and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400° to 425° or until brown.

title: dippity dogs
directions: You will need wooden skewers.

title: italian market soup(country:  italy)
directions: Boil rice as per package directions.
Rinse and cool.
While rice is cooling, prepare other ingredients.
Mix together; add rice and dressing.
Cool several hours before serving.

title: broccoli english walnut
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed and drain.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Melt butter (1/2 cup) and blend in flour and crushed chicken bouillon cubes.
Gradually add milk, stirring until thick and smooth.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine water and 6 tablespoons butter and heat until melted.
Pour over stuffing mix and toss together.
Add walnuts and spread over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hodgepodge soup
directions: Brown meat with onions, celery, and garlic.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes or longer.
I serve this with a tossed salad and hot cornbread for a complete meal.
It is especially good when the weather is cold.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine and put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Great for overnight company or when camping out.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cheese, milk and salt; stir well.
Add other ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight. Add additional mayonnaise just before serving, if desired.

title: guilt free mock tiramisu
directions: Pour 1/2 cup milk into blender.
Add cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Blend in remaining 1 cup milk.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt the margarine in a casserole dish, then add the sugar, flour and milk.
Mix.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: poor man's raisin cake
directions: Add flour, baking soda and powder.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: rita's cheese cake
directions: Blend graham crackers and mix with butter or margarine.
Press 3/4 of crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/4 for top.

title: greek potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl except fats and cheese.
Make patties.
Dip in grated cheese and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Use wide spatula to turn over. Salt and pepper to taste.
If broiling or baking is preferred, lay patties in buttered pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 450° for 15 minutes or broil until brown for approximately 10 minutes.
Serve plain or with yogurt or garlic sauce.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn meal and flour. Add unbeaten eggs and milk. Beat until sugar is dissolved. Stir in butter, lemon juice and rind. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce oven to 350° and bake 25 minutes.

title: how to boil water
directions: Put water in the tea kettle or pan and place on the burner on the stove.
Turn the burner to high.
At first it will seem that nothing is happening.
The water will just set there.
However, soon you will observe small bubbles on the bottom of the pan (inside). Then the bubbles will increase in number, become larger and begin to rise to the surface.
Now, we're getting somewhere!
Soon there will be more and more bubbles that rise to the surface faster and faster where they pop with amazing alacrity.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water, following label directions; drain and return to pot.
Stir in the cottage cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into a 6-cup baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken, cut in bite-size pieces.
Mix chicken, cream, and soup.
Pour into 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Add poppy seed; mix.
Pour crackers over chicken.
Melt butter.
Pour over.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (15 minutes with foil).

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool cake for 20 minutes.
Using a knife or the end of a wooden spoon, poke holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand evenly over top of cake.
Then pour caramel evenly over the top of your cake.
Let cool completely.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter dream pie
directions: Can use low calorie topping, cheese and peanut butter.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Thinly slice zucchini.
Arrange zucchini in baking dish, 9 x 5-inches (meat loaf pan is good).
Sprinkle zucchini with seasoned bread crumbs and oil.
Alternate layers, ending with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Pour in Mountain Dew or 7-Up and mix again.
Pour into molds and chill. Serve on lettuce leaf, if desired.
Garnish with whipped cream or mayonnaise.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix cream cheese and sausage.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Pinch together triangles to make one roll.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crescent dough.
Place in freezer until firm.
Slice and bake at 350°
until brown.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop tomato, onion, garlic and jalapeno pepper (scrape out the seeds) into about 1/2 -inch dice.
Loosely chop cilantro.
Cut avocados in half, then remove the pits.
Scoop the flesh out of the shells and place it in a food processor until smooth, then scrape into a bowl and stir in all ingredients, seasoning to taste.
Serve with chips.

title: m'm m'm vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: versatile quiche
directions: Cover bottom of pie crust with choice of meat.
Sprinkle the Swiss cheese over meat.
Sprinkle flour over the cheese.
Beat the remaining ingredients; pour over the cheese and meat.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until firm.

title: chicken katsu
directions: Start with three separate dishes or bowls.
In the first bowl, mix flour, garlic salt (to taste), salt and pepper (to taste).
In the second dish, scramble the eggs and add the water. In the third dish, place the Panko.
Heat the oil in a frying pan. Cut the chicken into long strips (it will help reduce the cooking time).
First dip the chicken into the egg batter, then into the flour.
Next, dip the chicken into the egg batter again and finally into the Panko.
Make sure all sides are well coated. Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with white rice, macaroni salad and Katsu sauce.

title: sugar-free date nut cake
directions: Blend eggs, butter, sweetener and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and spices, sifted together.
Mix well, then fold in the dates, applesauce and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan in a 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: martha washington's
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Roll into small balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolate chips.
Put toothpicks into balls and dip into chocolate mixture.
Let stand until firm.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion soup and tomato paste. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Scoop out a little of the seeds in squash. Fill squash with ground beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until squash is tender.
Top squash with American cheese.
When cheese is melted, serve.
You may serve with rice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add peanut butter until mixed well.
Add Cool Whip.
Save out enough Cool Whip to top pie with.
Put in pie crust.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend in a blender or mix with a mixer.
Store in one of the new all plastic jars (Skippy peanut butter).

title: dirt cake
directions: Make pudding and put aside.
Grind cookies in food processor or blender.
(Food processor works better than a blender.)
Mix cream cheese and sugar in a separate bowl; fold in pudding and whipped topping.

title: lemon refrigerator pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium size mixing bowl. Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate. If you want more color, use a drop or two of yellow food coloring.

title: pepper steak(heritage recipe)
directions: Salt and brown steak pieces on both sides, set aside.
Add onions, cook until tender.
Stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic. Cover and simmer 10 minutes till meat is tender.
Add green peppers, cook 5 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain well and salt to taste.
Add vegetables and olives.
Drizzle with desired amount of dressing.

title: coffee and cream dessert
directions: Dissolve coffee in hot water. Set aside. In a food processor bowl or blender container, combine cream cheese product, sugar, liqueur or orange juice and vanilla. Cover and process or blend until mixture is smooth. Transfer to a medium mixing bowl. Fold in whipped topping.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and shred potatoes.
Pat dry with paper towel.
In bowl, combine potatoes, egg, onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix.
In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Drop spoonful of mixture into hot oil.
Fry until edges are crisp; turn.
Serve with honey.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini, dry ingredients, vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch pans and bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add vegetables, soups, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and basil.
Mix well in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: petite cheesecake
