directions: Line muffin tin with cupcake papers.
Place one vanilla wafer (flat side down) in each paper.
Beat all the other ingredients until light and fluffy.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Peel away muffin cups.
Top with cherry or any other pie filling you desire.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, Karo and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: dark zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and brown sugar.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, zucchini and molasses.
Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add to zucchini mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured small loaf pans or in boiled cans for 1 hour at 350° or until center tests done with toothpick.
Cool in pans until bread will remove easily.

title: quick and easy cheese bean dip
directions: Heat chili.
Warm Cheez Whiz in microwave.
Add to chili. Serve with Doritos or any other nacho chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and break bud clusters into bite size pieces. In a small bowl, mix other ingredients, except bacon, and pour over broccoli.
Toss well to mix.
When ready to serve, mix in the bacon bits.

title: fruited turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients gently.
Serve on lettuce-lined salad plates.
(Mandarin oranges can be added for color.)

title: white wedding punch
directions: Mix juices together.
When ready to serve, put juice in punch bowl.
Add scoops of ice cream.
Pour in ginger ale.
Stir lightly.
Makes 30 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine beans, soup, milk, 1/2 can onions, 1/2 jar bacon bits and pepper.
Pour into a casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes. Top with the remaining onions and bacon bits.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Mash squash; add onion, 1/2 c. cracker crumbs, pepper, eggs, 1/4 c. butter, sugar and salt.
Mix well and pour into a buttered 2-qt. baking dish.
Melt remaining butter and spread on top. Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375
degrees for 1 hour.

title: noodle souffle *
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Beat eggs.
Mix noodles and eggs with all the other ingredients (except corn flakes and cinnamon) and put in a very large greased casserole.
Crush corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix.
Put 1/3 cake layer in bottom of punch bowl. Add can of pineapple, then add 1/2 of pudding.
Add another cake layer, pie filling, rest of pudding and then the other cake layer. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts, if you desire.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Make pudding according to directions in saucepan.
Blend dry cake mix into hot pudding with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into oiled 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle top with chocolate chips and nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May use different combination of cake mix, pudding and topping.

title: brown rice with mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: apple cake(fresh)
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let stand 30 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients into apple mixture.
Blend eggs and oil together. Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch floured pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Will be moist like fruit cake.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough in a 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan, pressing seams together to create a rectangular pizza crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Cool.

title: tofu manicotti
directions: Drain tofu.
Mash into fine consistency with fork.
Mix in George Washington broth and soy sauce.
Mix in thawed and drained spinach.
Stuff mixture into uncooked manicotti and place in greased baking dish.
Cover manicotti with spaghetti sauce and place overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, covered, about 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: goulash
directions: Lightly brown meat in large skillet.
Drain.
Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is transparent.
Add bell pepper, celery (chopped), tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer until pepper and celery are crisp-tender.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Dissolve soda in hot water.
Add to mixture.
Add dry ingredients and then nuts, chips and oatmeal.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Dissolve sugar and syrup over low heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until completely melted.
Add Special K cereal; stir.	Place in buttered 9 x 13 pan; press evenly.
Heat chocolate and butterscotch chips until melted.
Spread over cereal mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Add to flour and mix well, eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add and mix well the zucchini, nuts and raisins.

title: pesto pizza
directions: Spread pesto sauce evenly over pizza crust.
Mix Jack cheese and Mozzarella cheese together and sprinkle over pesto.
Layer on mushrooms over entire area.
Evenly distribute artichoke hearts and olives and garlic.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 425° oven for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and crust is brown.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan; add flour and brown. Add milk and cook until thickens.
Add carrots and cheese to mixture.
Put in casserole.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and spread over bread crumbs.
Bake in oven until bread crumbs are brown.

title: broccoli-grape salad
directions: Combine broccoli, grapes, raisins, celery, onion, and water chestnuts.
In separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt and honey. Pour over broccoli mixture and gently stir.
Serve.
Makes 3 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
If you use onions, bake a little longer.

title: easy all-in-one soup
directions: Saute ground beef and drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Or, browned meat and ingredients may be placed in crock-pot and cooked 2 or more hours.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix in blender; chill.
Excellent with fresh veggies.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Refrigerate any leftover pie.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sweeten to taste.
Mix flour, sugar and milk, then pour over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown (30 to 45 minutes).

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Spray glass baking pan with Pam.
Season each chicken breast with salt and pepper.
Place in baking pan.
Place 1 slice of Swiss cheese over each chicken breast.
Pour soup over chicken. Cover with stuffing mix.
Pour butter over stuffing mix.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Enjoy!!!

title: egg custard pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: toffee candy
directions: Spread 1 cup of walnuts on foil-lined tray.
Combine 1 cup sugar and 1 cup margarine (Blue Bonnet) and boil to 310°.
Pour mixture over nuts and immediately lay Hershey bars on top.
Spread with a knife until completely melted.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: belgian potato balls
directions: Grate raw potatoes.
Squeeze out the liquid in a cheesecloth, then measure amount.
Mix with same amount of mashed potatoes; add salt.
Start mixing in the flour (enough to form golf ball or smaller size balls).
Drop into rapidly boiling water.
Simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until they float to top.
Serve with roast pork or beef or roast chicken.
Can slice the next day and fry in butter.

title: baked fish
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons oil until golden brown. Add tomatoes, garlic, paprika, salt, lemon juice and remaining oil. Cook for about 20 minutes.
Place fish in baking dish and cover with sauce.
Bake in a 400° oven approximately 30 minutes.
Before serving, garnish with chopped parsley and lemon slices. Makes 4 servings.

title: country cabbage
directions: Cook the bacon in a large skillet over medium heat until browned. Remove bacon and crumble.
Add the cabbage and green pepper to skillet and cook over medium heat, stirring until soft about 15 minutes.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Put one box of raisins in pan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and then simmer 30 minutes.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add coffee and then boiled raisin water.
Add flour and spices.
Add raisins last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 bread tins.
A very old recipe.

title: sour cream zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini; do not pare.
Cut off ends; slice about 1/8-inch thick.
Cook in very small amount of water with all ingredients except sour cream until just tender.
Zucchini slices should not lose their shape; do not overcook.
Drain off water and add sour cream.
Toss, being careful not to break pieces.
Serves 6.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan, except frankfurters. Cover and simmer for at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add franks; simmer about 5 minutes.

title: korean flank steak
directions: Have the butcher tenderize the flank steak.
Cut into 2 or 3 pieces.
Mix
sugar,
soy
sauce
and garlic and marinate meat in it for 1/2 hour.
Coat with flour and dip into mixture of
green onion and
eggs.
Fry
in
medium
hot
oil.
Slice against grain and serve hot or cold.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, salt and shortening until crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add milk, eggs and grated apple; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pans.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: In a large pot, parboil head of cabbage until leaves may be removed carefully, one at a time.
In small skillet, saute mushrooms.
Put rice in large bowl.
Add mushrooms, celery, onion, parsley, sage and garlic powder, then add soy sauce.
Fill lower end of each leaf with stuffing and sprinkle grated cheese over the top of rice stuffing.
Roll leaf at once, folding sides of leaf toward center; continue rolling to end.
Tie with a string or secure with a toothpick.
Lay stuffed leaves side by side in a sprayed baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: millionaries candy
directions: Melt caramels with water.
Add pecans and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Melt chocolate in double boiler and add melted paraffin.
Pick up drops and dip in chocolate and paraffin.

title: sangria
directions: Put the top on the blender.

title: curried chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice, salt and pepper; mix well.
In a lightly greased 2-quart casserole, put a layer of half of the broccoli, a layer of half of the chicken and a layer of half of the soup
mixture; repeat layers.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood stuffed potatoes
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add shrimp, crabmeat, seasonings, sour cream, cheese, milk, chives and parsley.
Heat thoroughly over low heat.
Scoop out potato meat; cream with small amount of margarine and milk; add seafood mixture.
Stuff potato hulls and top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate sour cream frosting
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler over hot water. Stir constantly until completely melted. Remove from heat and beat in sour cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: deer salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Repeat this for 3 days in a row, mixing well each time.
Make 2 large or 3 small rolls.
Place on broiler rack or on a rack in a large pan so sausage can drain.
Bake 6 to 8 hours at 150°.
Salami forms its own "skin."

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients in an oven-safe glass loaf dish or loaf pan.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: company potatoes
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add the soup, potatoes and sour cream; spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine cheese and cornflakes and spread over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add corn, seasoning and flour. Stir to blend.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop by spoonfuls into skillet of hot fat.
Cook until brown, turning once.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 3 or 4 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup boiling water.
Stir well.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and oats.
Stir in egg.
Add shortening.
Add half of the flour.
Mix with spoon. Add rest of flour and knead by hand.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double, 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Form in 24 balls.
Place on greased pan.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet betty sausage dip
directions: Fry, crumble and drain sausage. Press to get out fat. Add cheese, cut into cubes with sausage, milk and salsa. Heat on low, stirring constantly, until melted. Serve with corn chips or Tostitos chips. Can serve in a small crock-pot.

title: mimi's peanut butter pie
directions: For crust, crush chocolate graham crackers; add butter and press into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° 10 minutes. Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients except additional topping and crushed Heath bars.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill overnight.
Top with extra topping and crushed bars.

title: sour cream and cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gently to creamed mixture. Mix well the pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: asparagus lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and cut in half crosswise.
In saucepan, cook garlic and thyme in butter.
Blend in flour; cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Season sauce with salt and pepper.
In buttered 2-quart microwavable dish, layer 1/3 of noodles, sauce, cheese, ham and asparagus.
Repeat layers twice.
In microwave, cover and cook on High 9 to 10 minutes, turning twice.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Combine buttermilk, oil and beaten eggs.
Beat well with dry ingredients.
This recipe will keep in covered container in refrigerator for at least 6 weeks. When ready to bake, pour into muffin pans and bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: "dirt" or oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos in heavy plastic bag or put in blender. Set aside. Mix powdered sugar, oleo and cream cheese together.
Set aside.

title: needhams
directions: Melt ingredients.
Use toothpicks to dip squares in hot chocolate.
Put on waxed paper to cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Take can of biscuits and cut each biscuit into four parts. Take white sugar and cinnamon and mix together.

title: whole wheat soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine whole wheat flour and white flour. For variety substitute any or all of the rolled oats and rolled rye cereal.
Also add the baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt. In a small bowl, combine egg, buttermilk, cooking oil and molasses.

Using a wooden spoon, combine the two mixtures, adding a bit more buttermilk if necessary to form a thick batter. Add raisins, if desired. Bake in two greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 375° until tops are quite brown. Excellent sliced thin and toasted!

title: egg cream
directions: Use 10-ounce glass.
Stir in chocolate and milk.
Slowly stir in enough soda to fill glass.
Yields 1 serving.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Put egg, salt and 3 tablespoons olive oil in blender.
Blend until mixture is light in color.
With blender on, pour in remaining olive oil in a slow, steady stream.
Stop pouring, only if the oil is not being absorbed.
If this occurs, blend without adding any more oil until oil is absorbed, then continue to add remaining oil.
Add lemon juice, blend briefly.
Adjust seasoning. Scrape into bowl.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Makes 3/4 cup.
Excellent and foolproof to make, this lasts for up to 1 week refrigerated.

title: peanut patties
directions: Let milk, sugar, syrup and butter melt.
Then add peanuts; cook and stir constantly until it reaches the soft ball stage. Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Drop by a spoon onto waxed paper.

title: squash casserole("magnifique")
directions: Dot the bottom of a casserole dish with 1/2 stick butter or margarine.
Line bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 bag of stuffing.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl; pour into casserole dish.
Top with the rest of the stuffing and the 1/2 stick butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or use a Bundt pan for 50 minutes.
Very good with cream cheese frosting.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mash the yolks with fork.
Stir in mustard, mayonnaise, salt, sugar and vinegar until thoroughly mixed.
Use a teaspoon to fill the whites with the yolk mixture.

title: martha washington's chocolate candy
directions: In large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients. Put into refrigerator to chill. Melt chocolate chips and wax in boiler. Roll chilled mixture into balls and dip in chocolate mixture. Put on wax paper to cool.

title: potato burgers
directions: Mix together potatoes, spices, hamburger, egg and onion, form into patties.
Fry in pan with a little oil until browned on bottom sides.
Put into cake pan and add cream of mushroom soup on top of patties.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Garnish with tomato slices and buttered bread crumbs the last 5 minutes of baking, if desired. Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: yellow squash muffins
directions: Wash squash thoroughly, trim off ends.
Cut squash in 1-inch slices.
Cook in small amount of boiling water 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain water and mash.
Measure enough squash to equal 2 cups.
Combine squash , eggs and margarine; stir well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl, making well in center of mixture; add squash mixture to dry ingredients stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix dream whip as directed on box. Set in refrigerator. Take fruit cocktail, add 1/2 cup water and bring to boil. Remove from heat, add Jello (dry) until dissolved.
Cut cream cheese in small bits and add to mixture.
Blend well.
Set in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Fold in dream whip and refrigerate. May use fat-free cream cheese.

title: strawberry rhubarb deep dish cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in strawberries, rhubarb, lemon juice and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until hot, bubbly and slightly thickened.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits; cut each in half.
Sprinkle biscuits with cinnamon-sugar.
Place on fruit.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until biscuits are golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Arrange in layers beginning with wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
End with pudding mixture on top.

title: decorator icing for a special cake
directions: Mix
at
high
speed until smooth.
Will ice a cake and for making borders and decorations.

title: steak roll-ups with mushrooms
directions: Cut steak into 6 pieces.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Prepare stuffing using package directions.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of stuffing on each piece of steak.
Roll up, securing with toothpicks.
Brown over medium heat in shortening in skillet for 2 minutes per side. Remove rolls and pour off excess drippings.
Add soup and 1 soup can water, stirring to mix well.
Return steak rolls to skillet, spooning sauce over each.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour, turning once.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter about 10 minutes.
Add to remaining ingredients and cook until thick.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Mix juice, eggs, flour and salt and cook until thick.
Add 1 1/2 dozen marshmallows.
Beat until cool.
Pour over cheese, pineapple and some nuts can be added, if you prefer.

title: round steak covered with onions
directions: Trim excess fat from steak; cut into serving size pieces. Season steak; dredge in flour.
Lightly pound floured steak. Brown steak in oil.
Add sliced onion; add water to cover steak. Cook on medium heat for 15 minutes.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Add water, if needed.

title: eleanor's cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in vanilla and sour cream.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix together. Set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion about 10 minutes (squash should be firm).
Drain well.
Combine squash with next 5 ingredients. Place in a 2-quart lightly greased casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine, sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: venison barbecue
directions: Fry meat in cooking oil or butter.
Mix rest of ingredients in a pan.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Add to meat and simmer.

title: indian fried bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add warm water slowly and mix.
Dough should be soft, not sticky.
Tear off a section the size of a peach.
Pat and stretch thin.
Poke a hole in the middle and fry.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Stir flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and shortening into fine crumbs. Remove 1/3 cup crumbs; set aside. Stir hot water and molasses into remaining mixture until blended. Pour into 9-inch cake pan. Remove square or round pan. Top with the reserved 1/3 cup of crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8+. Can do ahead.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and walnuts.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Fold Cool Whip and marshmallows into mayonnaise mixture.
Fold into apple mixture.
Chill.

title: maple walnut cream pie
directions: Combine maple syrup
and
milk
in
saucepan.
Beat egg yolks; add to saucepan.
Cook
and
stir
2 minutes on medium heat. Dissolve gelatin
in water.
Remove saucepan from heat. Stir in dissolved
gelatin
and maple extract.
Refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken.

title: salmon stew
directions: To assemble:
Saute onions in butter or margarine.
Add the whole can of salmon and the can of tomatoes (separate the bones from salmon and discard).
Cook onions, salmon and tomatoes with 1/2 cup water on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Lower heat and add diced, cooked potatoes.
Add another 1/2 cup of water.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Remove stew from heat and slowly add 2 tablespoons of evaporated milk.
Stir slowly until milk is mixed in stew. Then add the rest of the milk to which has been added 1 cup of water.
Reheat very slowly.
Add eggs (the stew will curdle if too hot).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squaw corn
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Drain all but 3 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
Cook and stir green pepper and onion in drippings until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir until eggs are thickened through but still moist.
Crumble bacon; sprinkle on egg mixture.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: three-cheese macaroni
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large heavy saucepan over low heat; whisk in flour until smooth. Cook, whisking constantly 1 minute. Gradually whisk in milk and next 3 ingredients; cook over medium heat, whisking constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat and whisk in cheeses until melted. Stir macaroni into cheese mixture and spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in a glass bowl in microwave at High 30 seconds. Stir in breadcrumbs and parsley. Sprinkle mixture over macaroni. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Let stand 10 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: macaroni and fruit dessert
directions: Cook the macaroni.
Strain the juice from the pineapple and oranges and save it.
Put in refrigerator.
Beat eggs, add sugar, salt, flour, and fruit juices with whisk.
Cook until thick.
In large container pour mixture over macaroni, mix well, cover and refrigerate over night.
Next day add Cool Whip, pineapple and oranges.
(cherries and walnuts can be added).

title: iced cucumber curls
directions: Drain off water and remove all ice cubes from cucumber.
Pour vinegar mixture on cucumbers.
Let set 24 hours.
Gets better the longer you wait.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake your cake as directed on box.
Let cool, then put on your pineapple filling or frosting.
Enjoy!!

title: date sticks
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs. Mix well. Add chopped nuts and dates. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cut into sticks and roll in granulated sugar while still warm.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture is cracker meal fine.
Stir in egg and water.
Use a rolling pin to roll out dough very thin on lightly floured board. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Drop squares in boiling chicken broth. Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Cover and cook on very low for 30 minutes.
You may add chicken pieces.

title: reeses peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix cookie dough according to recipe on the box or your own recipe.
Bake at temperature according to the recipe you are using.
Put 1 teaspoon full of dough into greased small or mini muffin tins and pat down.
Bake in oven for 6-7 minutes.
Take out and push a candy into the center of each cookie.
The dough will fill around the candy.
Bake another 4 minutes and remove from the oven.
Remove from tin when cookies cool or they will fall apart. You can place the entire tin the freezer to speed the cooling. Makes 3 dozen.

title: dumplings for chicken
directions: Put flour in mixing bowl.
Make a hole in the middle and put eggs in whole.
Pour in water or broth, stirring all the while you are pouring, and continue working in flour with fork until very stiff.
Then work with hands.
Work in all the flour you possibly can.
Put onto floured wax paper and roll thin.
Let dry out for an hour or two.
Turn over during drying time.

title: baked rabbit
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Place rabbit in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Melt butter and pour over rabbit. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with foil and bake until tender 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Pour off liquid and use to make gravy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water; drain.
Beat egg; mix with broccoli.
Add soup; mix well.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top, then cover with buttered crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes, until cracker crumbs are golden.

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cut bread into cubes and put in dish.
Sprinkle on margarine, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Beat eggs with remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over bread. Put baking dish in a pan containing 1 inch hot water and bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Drain veggies and blot dry on paper towels.
Add to cheese mixture.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces. Discard (eat) ends.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place everything in blender at one time.
Blend until mixed together.
Pour into a 10-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
When done, the crust will be on bottom, custard in the middle and coconut on top.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda and add to cream mixture, alternating with yogurt.
Add mashed bananas and nuts last, mixing until well blended.
Spoon into 2 loaf pans or 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in greased pan.

title: quick delicious chili
directions: Presto (20 mins.)
In separate pan:
melt 1/4 cup butter (1/2 cube).
Optional:
Saute 1 cup sliced mushroom.
Add 1/2 cup flour and brown lightly.
Slowly add juice from meat (as though making gravy).
Add 1 tsp. steak sauce.
Add 3/4 cup sour cream 1/4 at a time until thoroughly mixed.
When thoroughly heated, add beef pieces and stir.

title: easy crispy melt appetizers
directions: Arrange Nabisco Triscuit wafers on microwave-safe serving plate.
Put one teaspoon of pizza sauce on each wafer.
Then add some Mozzarella cheese to each wafer.
You can add more toppings, if desired.
Microwave on High until cheese melts or place in conventional oven on broil until cheese melts.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrot and pepper.
Add to sweet pickle juice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise; mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: justin cookies
directions: Spread frosting on graham cracker.
Top with another graham cracker and frost.
Decorate with your favorite topping.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut meat into serving pieces. Pound 1 1/2 tablespoons flour and salt into meat. Brown meat in hot shortening. Place meat in shallow baking dish. Blend remaining 1/2 tablespoon flour with drippings in skillet. Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Pour mixture over meat. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Remove from oven. Top with cheese and serve.

title: chinese noodle candy
directions: Heat chocolate and butterscotch chips in double boiler until melted.
Add noodles until well blended.
With large tablespoon, drop into single clusters on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Cool. Mix pudding according to directions and spread on cooled cake. Cover cake and pudding
with
bananas
sliced round.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed pecans.

title: mom's brownies(microwave)
directions: Place butter and cocoa in an 8-inch round cake pan.
Microwave on High, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until butter melts.
Stir in sugar first.
Add rest of ingredients in order and mix.
Cover with glass lid.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Rotate 1/2 turn and microwave on High 2 minutes.
If top is still wet, turn and microwave 1 more minute.
Let set with lid off or slide paper towel inside to keep moisture off the top.

title: microwave zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Cook onion and butter in covered casserole until tender (about 3 to 4 minutes).
Add the juice from the tomatoes and reduce by boiling, uncovered, in microwave.
Add the zucchini and cook until almost tender.
Add tomatoes and seasonings and cook, covered, until heated through, another 7 minutes.

title: chicken l'orange
directions: Saute chicken in 1 teaspoon oil until no longer pink.
In a saucepan, combine juice, zest and sugar and bring to the boil. Add starch, dissolved in a little juice.
Stir until smooth.
Add pieces of orange.

title: mayonnaise buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour and mayonnaise (mix well).
Pour small amounts of milk to flour mixture.
Mix until fairly smooth.
Sprinkle hands with flour.
Make roll dough with hand, forming a ball.
Place on a cookie sheet and cook until golden brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples and set aside.
Measure oil, then add sugar and eggs; mix at low speed until creamy.
Sift flour; measure, then sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture in small amounts.
Beat well after each addition.
When batter becomes stiff, finish by hand.
Fold in chopped pecans, apples and vanilla.
Can be spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 to 60 minutes.
Avoid overbaking.
This can be made into muffins, also.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix with mixer and bake in 4 small loaf pans at 325° for 35 minutes. Freezes well.

title: all in the pot
directions: Place ingredients in layers in a well-greased baking dish. Cover with the can of tomato soup diluted in a can of water. Cover the dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and cook 1/2 hour more.

title: nette's morning glory muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins, apples and nuts.
Beat eggs with oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: Brown beef with half of the bag of seasoning and drain.
Heat the beans with the other half of the seasoning.
Put a thin layer of chips on tray.
Drop by teaspoon the beef and beans.
Scatter a handful of both cheeses on top, along with a few onions.
Do layers of this until your pile is about 4 or 5-inches tall.
Bake at 375° until cheese has melted, about 15 minutes.
Garnish with salsa, sour cream, more onions and hot peppers if you prefer.

title: acorn squash
directions: Prick squash - pour half the liquid in each half of squash. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and bake an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
About 10 minutes before done, add sliced apple.
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: blueberry stack cake
directions: Slice bananas on top.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: cajun coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage and refrigerate overnight. Next day, shred cabbage and toss well with dressing.

title: smothered onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in the margarine until they are soft.
Place onions in a large casserole dish; sprinkle with the Swiss cheese. Combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat on the stove until thickened.
Pour over onions.
Top with some of the stuffing; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, pineapple and liquid and bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Roll out thin.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 450°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers into bowl.
Add sour cream. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix until combined.

title: horseshoe cookies
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt until crumbly.
Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Put eggs in yeast mixture and add to flour and Crisco mixture.
Put in large greased bowl, cover tightly and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: crab or tuna delight
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Warm soup and simmer.
Add the softened gelatin and cream cheese. Stir over medium heat until dissolved (about 3 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add mayonnaise, celery, crab meat or tuna, chopped onion and parsley.
Rinse ring mold in cold water.
Pour mixture into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold on cold serving platter.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, chiles, soup and 1 cup of cheese.
Divide chicken evenly among tortillas.
Put about 1/4 c. sour cream mixture in each tortilla.
Roll up burrito style.
Place in 9x13 pan.
Cover with remaining sour cream mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Can also be layered in crock pot.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put peanut butter and butter in bowl with wooden spoon.
Stir in syrup and vanilla. Add sugar one cup at a time to peanut butter mixture until well blended.
Knead fudge until creamy and pat evenly into pan.
Chill in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: caramel icing
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, combine butter, brown sugar, and salt.
Boil two minutes stirring constantly.
Add milk and return to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add powdered sugar and beat until thick enough to spread.
Add vanilla.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: gotabki(cabbage rolls)
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Place whole head in large kettle filled with boiling water.
Cover.
Cook 3 minutes.
Remove softened outer leaves. Repeat until all large leaves have been removed (about 20 leaves).
Cut thick center stem from each slice.

title: marinated brie
directions: Cook basil, peppercorns and sliced garlic in the oil until it starts to bubble.
(Do not overcook, or the garlic will burn.) Remove from heat; allow to cool.
Place sliced Brie on the bottom of a shallow dish.
Pour the marinade over to cover cheese.
Allow to stand for at least 4 hours before serving.
Arrange 2 or 3 slices of cheese on salad leaves; just before serving, dribble with marinade.
Serves 6.

title: ganmodoki
directions: Wrap tofu with paper towel.
Place a weight on it; wait about 30 minutes until water comes out.

title: sara's super brownies
directions: Follow directions on box and mix up box of brownie mix along with eggs, water and oil.
After mixed up good, add Reeses pieces and mix them up good too.
Then put in oven and bake for however long the box says to.
After baked, ice the brownies.
Then put on pecans and then eat!

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Combine in covered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add water if necessary.
Place over cooked noodles.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and chop.
Mix all ingredients and microwave 3 minutes.
Mix and serve with crackers.

title: dill crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put onto cookie sheets in a single layer.
Bake in warm oven (200°) for 15 to 20 minutes. Turn occasionally with spatula.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn.
Mix and boil sugar, oleo and salt for five minutes.
Take off heat and add vanilla and soda.
Pour over popped corn and nuts, mixing well in deep roaster type pan.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts, beating well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
With a fork dipped in sugar, press tops of cookies.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Place on rack to cool.

title: pioneer ham casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: missouri baked ham
directions: Simmer ham for 1 hour. Trim fat.

Place ham in baking pan, trimmed side up. Score. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Stud with cloves and spread brown sugar over ham. Add mustard and 1 1/2 cups boiling water to vinegar. Pour into baking pan. Cover. Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: heavenly casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Set aside. Cook macaroni noodles according to directions.
Add to meat/sauce mixture.
Set aside.
Beat together sour cream and cream cheese. Add sliced green onions.
In a 13 x
9-inch pan, layer 1/2 noodle and meat/sauce mixture on bottom.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top; layer remaining meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches.
Bring juice, sugar, vinegar and spices to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes to melt sugar.
Remove from heat and add peach halves. Cool. Refrigerate.

title: fruited punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine iced tea mix, orange juice and water. Add blueberries, strawberries, peaches, bananas and cherries. Also, add the reserved syrup.
Chill.
Just before serving, add club soda.

title: tourlou (greek vegetables)
directions: Combine and spread first 7 ingredients in 16 x 13-inch pan. Pour olive oil over all.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (covered with lid or foil).
After 1 hour, stir.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 1 hour longer, or until fairly thick.
Serve hot or cold.
May be frozen.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: practically instant minestrone
directions: Note:
You will need a big pot for this.

title: black-eyed susans
directions: Melt butter in regular cake pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and sugar in with butter and pat down.
Layer coconut, then chocolate chips and then nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all and let sit for about 15 minutes.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour in greased tube pan. Cook at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: south of the border hot cocoa
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside. Heat 1 cup milk until bubbly; do not boil. Gradually whisk in the cocoa mixture until smooth. Gradually stir in remaining milk.
Remove from heat; whisk in cream and vanilla. Yields 5 cups.

title: creamed kohlrabi
directions: Peel and slice kohlrabi into 1/4-inch saucer-like slices.
Put kohlrabi in pot of water.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt and bring to a boil.
Lower the flame and fork test kohlrabi until soft (not mushy).
Drain kohlrabi (as if it were spaghetti).
In a small saucepan, melt butter and add milk.
Let both ingredients warm slowly.
Slowly add flour and stir until a thick consistency appears.
Add an additional tablespoon of milk.
Mix and turn off. Pour sauce over kohlrabi and serve.
Taste before adding salt and pepper.

title: corn bread pudding
directions: Melt butter or margarine; pour into casserole (1 1/2-quart). Mix eggs and sour cream with wire whisk in dish until smooth.
Add corn.
Pour muffin mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and cut each apple in 8 pieces, then cook in microwave 2 minutes. Unroll dough, putting 1 apple piece in each triangle. Wrap and seal edges. Place in a 9 x 13 pan. Heat oleo, sugar and cinnamon (in microwave 3 minutes), then pour over dumplings. Pour Mt. Dew in bowl and add 1 tablespoon cornstarch to thicken; pour over everything else. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry honey butter
directions: In a food processor, puree strawberries; force the puree through a fine sieve into a saucepan; add honey and lemon juice. Boil mixture, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes or until thickened.
Cool to room temperature.
In a bowl, cream together the butter and strawberry mix.
Let mixture stand for 1 hour, covered, in a cool place so that flavors can mix and develop. Serve with croissants or toast.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time beating after each.
Add vanilla and chocolate, mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Alternately add sifted dry ingredients and butter milk to chocolate.
Mix after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter in pans lined on the bottom with paper.
Bake 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, carrots and pickle relish.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Top with shoestring potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir together; do not beat.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chess pie
directions: Put in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until solid.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Use only 9 pieces (1/2 box) lasagne.
Cook as directed on box, drain.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, water, salt and celery seed; bring to a boil.
After the mixture cools, pour over the vegetables.
Can be kept in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: judy turner's 5 day pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions and layer in jar.
Boil ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers in jar and let sit until cool. Put in refrigerator.
Every day flip jar over a couple of times for 5 days.
Store in fridge.
Enjoy!

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Add salt, paprika and flour. Batter will be stiff.
Fold in thirds; roll out and cut in thin strips.
Twist and lay on cookie sheet.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: First layer chicken in pan.
Mix Veg-All, soup and broth well. Pour over chicken.
Mix milk, flour and butter well.
Pour over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: mother's pear conserve
directions: Remove seeds from lemon and oranges.
Grind pulp and rind, using the coarse blade of food chopper.
Combine fruits and sugar. Cook slowly, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Pear conserve can be used instead of mincemeat.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and bananas and blend well. Add milk with vinegar (may be curdled).
Fold in flour mixture and milk alternately.
Stir in nuts; blend well.
Will make 2 small or 1 large loaf pan.
Oil pan and bake 1 hour.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese.
Mash pimentos and add juice left in can.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: burger casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef.
Cook celery and onion until tender; drain fat.
Add soup and salt.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Round potatoes around edge of casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: san juan squash
directions: Slice squash in half lengthwise and scoop out seeds.
Parboil for 10 minutes.
Put in single layer in shallow pan; sprinkle with salt (chili powder also), chopped onion and bread crumbs.
Top each half with bacon slice or cooked carne adobado.
Bake at 350° with water just to cover bottom of pan until squash is tender and bacon is browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour mixture into greased square pan.
Cook approximately 350.
Remove from oven when lightly brown.
It will still be gooey.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut up onion, green pepper and garlic; saute in butter. Combine remaining ingredients; simmer for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine juice and next 4 ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, just until moistened.
Fold in chocolate mini-morsels.
Spoon, filling 2/3 full into paper-lined muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: chocolate macadamia morsels
directions: Mix together Basic Batch, chocolate and nuts.
Beat egg with vanilla and milk.
Add to dry mixture; blend well.
Knead dough slightly with hands to fully mix.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 6 to 8 minutes. Immediately remove from baking sheet.
Yields 4 dozen 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Cut cabbage.
Place in jars.
Add salt to quart and fill with water.
Add a small piece of hot pepper at the top, if desired. Make on light of moon when signs are in the knees.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes approximately 20 (1 1/2-inch) meatballs.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Then mix the pudding-milk mixture and the Cool Whip-cream cheese mixture together.
Pour into long cake pan that has bottom lined with graham cracker squares.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top of pudding mixture and ice with frosting.
Chill and serve.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Combine pineapple chunks, cheese, sugar, and flour.
Pour into 8x8 buttered baking dish.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add crushed tomato. Bring to a simmer and add sugar. Then add salt, bay leaves and as much oregano, basil and pepper as you like. Heat all together and remove bay leaves before serving.

title: refrigerator pickle pot
directions: Using a crinkle cutter, cut cucumbers into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Set aside.
Cut carrots with crinkle cutter into 1-inch chunks.
Set aside.
Trim cauliflower and separate into florets. Set aside.
Quarter the onions if they are larger than 1-inch in diameter.
Cut green tomatoes into quarters.
Drop carrots, cauliflower and onions into boiling water for 2 minutes in several batches if necessary.
Layer all the vegetables in a gallon jar, placing the garlic cloves in the middle.
Sprinkle with dill weed, if used.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and salt until blended.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cool and dice potatoes.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry. Remove from pan.
Fry onions until done.
Pour off half of bacon grease and combine onions and bacon.
Add the dressing, sugar and vinegar and bring to a slow boil, stirring well.
Pour over potatoes and heat to serve.
It's better left overnight to marinate.
Before serving, warm it through in oven.

title: turkey medallions with orange teriyaki sauce
directions: Saute celery, onion, salt and ginger in oil.
In bowl, mix turkey, horseradish and sauteed mixture plus chopped parsley.
Make 8 patties and cook in oil.
In 1 inch of water cook carrots about 5 minutes.
Stir in pea pods; cover and cook 2 minutes longer.
In cup, mix juice, teriyaki sauce, flour, 1 tablespoon chopped parsley and 1/3 cup water.
Stir into skillet from which patties have been cooked.
Loosen browned bits from pan, boil 1 minute.
Place patties and vegetables on platter; pour orange over all.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: crab mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add to warm, undiluted soup.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 1-quart mold. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together peanut butter, brown sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add melted chocolate and chocolate chips.
Stir in flour and baking soda.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes at 300°.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onion fine.
Just cover with boiling water. Let stand 5 minutes.
Add more boiling water and let stand for 10 minutes more.
Drain well.
Add vinegar, salt, sugar and 1 quart of water.
Cook on a simmer or until thick and done.
Put in sterile airtight jars.

title: cheesy zucchini lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella cheese. Mix remaining Mozzarella cheese, the zucchini, Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Spread 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch or 12 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch.
Top with 3 of the noodles.
Spread half of the cheese mixture over noodles in dish.
Top with 3/4 cup of spaghetti sauce.
Repeat with 3 noodles, remaining cheese mixture and 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce.
Top with remaining noodles and spaghetti sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake about 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with reserved Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Mash shrimp.
Add all other ingredients, except bread.
Mix. Cut crusts from bread.
Spread with shrimp mixture.
Cut into triangles.
Deep fry until golden brown.
May be frozen after frying and reheated in broiler.

title: vegetable pizza(great snack!)
directions: Press crescent rolls on the bottom of a 9 x 11-inch cookie sheet.
Bake as directed on package.
Cool slightly.
Beat together cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion, dill weed and seasoned salt.
Spread on crescent roll crust.
Sprinkle with various chopped vegetables.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 cup chopped pecans.
Layer coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed; pour over coconut.
Melt butter; add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix; knife through.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Measure and sift dry ingredients.
Mix molasses with hot water.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid, a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Bake in paper lined or greased 11 x 7-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with chocolate icing, if desired.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugar and egg yolks.
Sift flour and soda together.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 or 4 (9-inch) prepared layer cake pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: betty's fruit salad
directions: Use any kind of fruit you like and as much as you want.
Mix Equal to your taste.
If frozen fruit, let thaw out in refrigerator for about a day and night or until thawed.
Drain. Mix all fruit together.
Add Equal to taste, then add nuts and miniature marshmallows.
Mix all together and let set 1 or 2 hours in refrigerator so Equal can soak in, then eat.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Pour Minute rice over bottom of greased oblong 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Heat cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup with milk until barely warm.
Pour over rice; make sure all rice is mixed in with soup mixture.
Place cut-up chicken on top with rice mix.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in pan.
Mix cake mix as per directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done in center.

title: bite size pizza
directions: Roll biscuit dough on floured surface into 4-inch circles. Place on baking sheet.
Spoon tomato sauce onto dough.
Sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder.
Spread sausage over sauce. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 10 servings.

title: kidney bean-macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni in salted boiling water.
Drain well.
Saute onion in margarine.
Remove from heat and add soup.
Stir in milk gradually.
Add kidney beans, seasonings and 2 slices of the cheese.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Mix in macaroni.

title: chocolate gem
directions: Dissolve chocolate in 1/4 to 1/3 cup of water.
Add milk to fill cup.
Mix margarine and sugar together.
Add beaten egg and mix together, then add all other ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake is done in a loaf pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter until soft.
Mix all other ingredients into saucepan.
Add cooked onions.
Cook over medium heat until thick, as desired.

title: meatball curry
directions: Soak bread in water and squeeze most of the water out and mix all of the other ingredients together.

title: mamma st. clair's rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar and Crisco and bring to a boil, then cool. Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.

title: fresh cherry salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Put in cherries and jello. Add Pepsi and pineapple.
Let thicken in 9 x 9-inch pan.
May top with cream cheese and Cool Whip.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Put noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chicken mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard together.
Add meat and cheese.
Mix well and pour over bread.
Toss lightly.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes after you take from oven.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut uncooked biscuits into quarters. In a small bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and biscuits. Put into a buttered Bundt pan. Combine brown sugar and butter. Pour the mixture over the biscuit mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. When slightly cooled, turn the Bundt pan upside-down
to release the bread on a plate. Peel apart to eat.

title: lentil roast
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add more bread crumbs if a drier loaf is desired.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with gravy, if desired.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter; mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs, melted oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread evenly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat down.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly, spooning off fat.
Add sausage, tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic, basil and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Place half of cooked noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread on half of the cheese mixture and cover with half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce. Repeat layers about twice more.
Bake at 375° for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: quaker oats meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef.
Mix well.
Add ground beef.
Bake in loaf dish 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon and cloves into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and nuts and mix well.
Beat eggs in small bowl.
Add oil all at once and beat well.
Add 1/3 of egg and oil mixture to dry ingredients at a time and mix after each addition.
Peel and dice apples and add to mixture; mix well.
Bake in 13 x 9 1/4 x 2-inch pan which has been greased and floured for 1 hour at 350°.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Combine ground veal, egg and bread crumbs; form into patties (hamburger size).
Brown patties on both sides in oil in frying pan.
Remove from pan; drain on paper towels.
Place patties in an ungreased baking dish in a single layer.
Top each with a slice of Provolone cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce over and between patties until slightly covered.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients together and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat the eggs, sugar, margarine and vanilla together for about 4 minutes.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Spread pineapple over cream mixture.
Arrange bananas over pineapple.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with pecans. Cover and refrigerate 6 hours.
Garnish with cherries.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Spray a large non-stick frying pan with nonfat cooking spray. Saute the onion and garlic in chicken broth.
Add the basil and other seasonings.
Add chicken and saute about 7 minutes or until the chicken is cooked.
Add the zucchini and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Add the fettuccine and milk.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and mix well.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Arrange chops in baking dish (single layer). Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Combine brown sugar, apple juice, soy sauce, ketchup, cornstarch. Core apple and cut into 3/4 inch thick rings. Turn chops. Place one apple ring on each chop. Spoon some sauce over each chop. Return chops to oven and bake for 30 minutes more or until chops are done.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice large, peeled onions about 1/4 inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Soak rings about 15 minutes in milk and drain slightly.
Beat egg and add fresh milk.
Roll rings in flour, then egg mixture and then in bread crumbs.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on absorbent towels.
Fry at 365°.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: In an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix ingredients. Cover and bake for 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: toad-in-the-hole
directions: Mix everything but sausage in a blender.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook sausages.
Arrange sausages in single layer in a 6 x 10 x 2-inch dish at least 1-inch apart. Moisten with 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Pour batter over sausages and bake 30 minutes or until browned.
Serve at once.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients. Keep in tightly closed containers.
Makes almost a quart of mix.

title: low-fat chocolate shake
directions: Place milk and syrup in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed.
Blend for 2 seconds.
Add frozen yogurt.
Cover and blend on low for 5 seconds or until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate and set aside.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, chocolate and vegetable oil.
Mix well; add dry ingredients, zucchini and nuts.
Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar or put frosting on.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; set aside.
To assemble, spread bean dip in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Cover with seasoned avocado mixture and sprinkle with chopped onions and tomatoes. Spread sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mixture.
Sprinkle over all with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: special breakfast bread
directions: Cut up loaf and roll into balls.
Place into tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Pour over butter, then sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Top with nuts.
Place pan in oven to let rise during the night.
In the morning, turn oven on to 350°.
Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: sour cream apple cake
directions: Mix everything but the apples.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Put half the batter in pan.
Layer with apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add rest of batter, then apples and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans(quick and easy)
directions: Bake, covered, in greased casserole at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and continue baking for 20 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Chop onion and green pepper fine. Drain grease.
Save 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion and pepper and rice until golden brown, then add bacon.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Place in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sausage meat, Bisquick, cheese and paprika.
Form into small balls!
Place on cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix; press in buttered 12 x 9 x 3-inch pan.

title: hot artichoke cheese dip
directions: Drain, rinse and chop artichokes.
Cream together remaining ingredients. Fold in chopped artichokes.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 or 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: punch
directions: Pour Slice over sherbet in punch bowl.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Cool until partially thickened. Fold in Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Pour into mold.
Cool.

title: cracker salad
directions: Break saltines in a bowl, add tomatoes, onion, green bell pepper, cheddar cheese and moisten with mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.
Serve while crackers still have some crunch.

title: aku salad
directions: Cut aku into bite size pieces.
Then fry aku with flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until brown.
Let cool.
Then add remaining ingredients to aku.
Mix well.

title: brownie pie
directions: Bake pie crust in 400° oven until lightly browned.
Mix all ingredients
in
a bowl with a fork.
Pour into pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: bakery icing
directions: Blend shortening, margarine, sugar and vanilla thoroughly. Add milk to mixture until of spreading consistency.
May store in refrigerator about a week.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove tops and seeds from green pepper. Parboil 5 minutes and drain.
Brown meat and onion in hot fat. Add tomatoes, corn and seasoning. Pour hot butter or margarine over bread crumbs separate.
Stuff pepper with ingredients and top with butter bread crumbs.
Stand upright in greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Add small amount of water.
Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: poor man's pepper steak
directions: Mix beef, pepper and onion together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Make patties and fry.
Lay in a single layer in a baking dish.
Top with the soup and 1/2 can of water.
Bake at 350° until gravy is bubbly.
Serve with rice.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions, using layer pan.
Mix sour cream, coconut and sugar together.
Set 1 cup of mixture to side.
When cake layers have cooled, split and fill with the remaining sour cream, coconut and sugar mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: john's great chunky salsa
directions: Place olive oil in large glass bowl.
Mince garlic and add to oil.
Under broiler, roast New Mexico chilies; be sure to turn them just when the skins begin to turn black.
Roast on other sides, then place them in paper bag for 5 minutes.
Peel and remove stems, veins and seeds, then chop them and add to bowl along with jalapenos.

title: mary's masterpiece
directions: Roll sausage and round steak in flour seasoned with garlic, salt and pepper; brown sausage and then round steak in oil.
Add onion, then soup mix.
Cover with water; let simmer 2 hours or until tender.
Serve over white rice.
Yummy!

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt the wax in a pan until melted on low heat.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted; add peanut butter and stir until mixed well and has no lumps.
Add Rice Krispies; mix well and add chopped nuts.
Pour into well buttered pan (8 x 8-inch) and let cool.
You may also use white chocolate morsels.

title: hot turkey hustle-up(tasty casserole for leftover turkey)
directions: Combine ingredients in a 9 to 10-inch greased casserole dish.

title: hot dog slaw
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.

title: homemade breading
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in an airtight container.
Plan on 1/2 to 1 tablespoon of the breading for each chicken or fish piece.
Calories per serving: 25.
Exchanges: 1/3 starch.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix. Press in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl and serve over bed of lettuce.
To lower fat, use low-fat mayonnaise.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and lard, then add eggs.
Add peanut butter, then add flour and soda, sifted together.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Take 1 teaspoon dough and make into round balls.
Lay in pan. Crisscross top of balls with a fork, both ways.
Bake at 350°.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Blend together but do not put in final container until almost thick.
Fold in mold.
Mold at least 4 hours.

title: hot fudge sauce(can be used as base for frosting.)
directions: Mix ingredients except vanilla in a heavy saucepan. Stir and bring to full rolling boil for 3 minutes. Add vanilla and cool.

title: garfish balls
directions: Mix fish with seasonings.
Make balls and roll lightly in flour.
Fry until brown in small amount of oil.
Add little vinegar before adding water to fish balls.
Then add water to cover the fish; let cook until done and the water is almost gone.
Leave enough for gravy.

title: crab casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in milk, croutons, cheese, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Place chunks of crabmeat in casserole and do the same with spinach so that when cut, each person will get some in each square.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can use broccoli or asparagus instead of spinach.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: ellen's cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add 2 tablespoons of sour cream, 1 teaspoon vanilla and almond flavoring.
Beat egg whites separately adding 1 cup sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff, then fold into cheese mixture; pour into spring-form pan lined with crust and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes, then mix remaining sour cream with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; spread on cake and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake additional 5 minutes at 425°.
Cool away from drafts; chill and remove sides of pan.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: okra pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour over okra, with 1 garlic clove and 1 hot pepper in each jar. Seal jars.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Pour in long flat greased and lined pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes (glass at 325°).

title: pie crust
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix the water, egg and vinegar.
Add to the first mixture all at once.
Mix by squeezing with your hands.
Makes 6 to 7 crusts.

title: whole  wheat bread
directions: In a small bowl, mix and dissolve first three ingredients. Set aside ten minutes.
Beat egg in small bowl with a fork, set aside.
Melt butter in microwave.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine flours, sugar, and salt.
Add yeast, egg, butter, and warm water.
Begin combining and continue to knead all for ten minutes.
Fold, press, turn, adding small amounts of flour as needed.
Return to large bowl.
Cover with towel, and let rise at room temperature (75-80°) for 2 hours.
Punch down, knead a little.
Grease 4 pans.
Shape dough into 4 pans.
Cover, let rise 1 1/2 hour.
Bake at 375° (to 400°) from a cold oven 15 minutes. Watch closely.
Bread will slightly brown on top.

title: daddy's delight - venezuelan quesillo
directions: *Or you can substitute 1 cup of shredded coconut.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and mound on serving dish.
Mix ketchup and horseradish.
Spoon around mold.
Serve with Waverly Wafers.

title: peach crisp
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add salt and butter or margarine.
Mix together with hands or fork or pastry blender until mixture looks real crumbly.
Spread drained peaches evenly in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle the crumb mixture evenly on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 400°.
Top should be golden brown.
Serve warm or use favorite topping.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: one dish chicken
directions: In roaster pan, place dry rice mix.
Add both cans of soup and water.
Stir gently to blend.
Place chicken on top and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Check once in awhile for liquids; may need to add a little water.

title: pineapple upside-down french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a saucepan melt butter over moderate heat and stir in sugar and pineapple, stirring until sugar dissolves.
In shallow bowl whisk together eggs, milk and salt. In baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch) spread pineapple mixture evenly over bottom.
Dip bread slices into milk mixture in batches and arrange in one layer on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake French toast in middle of oven 20 to 25 minutes or until bread is golden. Cool French toast in pan 1 minute.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: white sauce and veggies
directions: Soften cream cheese by warming on low over stove top.
Add all other ingredients, being careful not to add too much chicken broth, making the sauce too thin.
(Should be consistency of spaghetti sauce.)
Parmesan, pepper, lemon juice and white wine can be used according to taste.
Mix with vegetables and serve over your favorite pasta.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken, shred, and set aside.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Combine cookie crumbs with 2 sticks oleo. Scatter across bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Mix fruit together in a large bowl.

title: maple walnut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking without stirring until 300°. Butter a large cookie sheet and remove syrup from heat.
Stir in nuts, butter, soda and flavoring.
Mix and pour onto sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk, pecans, pineapple, lemon juice and coconut.
Pour into pie crust and let chill in refrigerator.

title: mumbo jumbo
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add bananas to chilled mixture right before serving.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra firmly into hot sterilized jars.
Put 1 garlic bud in each jar.
Bring remaining ingredients to a rolling boil.
Pour brine over okra and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: On stove, mix butter, sugar and pecans. Pour over graham crackers. Bake at 350° about 5 minutes until starts to bubble. Take out of oven and let set.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients together and pat into well-greased jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch) or large cake pan. Bake about 10 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
While warm, frost with chocolate chips and peanut butter melted together.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash and pull skin off chicken.
Dip in dressing.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Place on aluminum foil on baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(You can use livers and gizzards.)

title: macaroni english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: almond coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour batter into pie pan lined with 2 layers of tinfoil (shiny side up).
Cover top with almonds and sprinkle on sugar.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Wait until cake cools before removing.

title: shrimp with herbed jalapeno cheese
directions: Plunge shrimp into large saucepan of boiling lightly salted water and cook for about 45 seconds, or until they turn pink. Drain, refresh under cold water; pat dry.
In food processor or blender, blend cream cheese, garlic, chilies, coriander, salt and pepper to taste until smooth.
Transfer to bowl and chill for about 30 minutes, until firm.
Transfer the mixture to a pastry bag fitted with a small star tip and pipe it into the slit of each shrimp.
Chill shrimp on a plate for 1 hour.
Makes 25 hors d'oeuvres.

title: apple fritters
directions: Blend flour, milk and egg together.
Stir in apples.
Drop from teaspoon into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown, 2 to 5 minutes. Drain and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: flank steak
directions: Combine together and pour over meat.
Marinate overnight. Drain meat.
Broil about 2 minutes on each side or barbecue on an outside grill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo and Velveeta cheese in pan.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and powdered sugar, 1/3 at a time.
Put in pan and freeze for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Layer continuously in this order:
chopped cabbage, hamburger and pinch of salt and pepper. Top with undiluted tomato soup and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
and
onion.
Place in casserole dish. Add undiluted
soups
and
cooked peas.
Mix together.	Place Tater Tots or cubed potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with cheese during last 15 minutes of baking.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Mix with remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator for several hours.
Serve cold.

title: nana's chicken
directions: Mix first 3 items in bowl.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover for 20 minutes.
Serve with angel hair pasta or over white rice.

title: slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar over shaved cabbage and chopped onion.
Mix in other ingredients and chill.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and cocoa.
Set aside.
Cream together eggs and sugar and add oil, butter, milk, vinegar and red food coloring.
Add dry ingredients slowly until all dry ingredients are incorporated.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.

title: mofongo(plantains and pork crackling)
directions: Peel plantains and cut into diagonal slices, about 1-inch thick.
Place plantains and diced salt pork in a pot with water to cover.
Let soak for 10 minutes.
Drain and wipe dry both plantains and salt pork.
Place salt pork in a hot skillet or frying pan (no extra oil is necessary).
Stir-fry over high heat until pieces are browned and crisp (about 5 minutes) and put aside.
This is known as the chicharron or pork crackling.

title: skillet squash medley
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter and brown sugar.
Add butternut squash.
When squash is a little tender, add remaining squash and nutmeg.
Cook over medium heat until crisp-tender, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: root beer
directions: Mix sugar, extract, yeast and 1/2 cup water together.
Stir until sugar has dissolved.
Add 3 quarts water.
Put in bottles, let stand in sun 3 hours.

title: pickled peaches or pears
directions: Make a syrup of vinegar and sugar.
Add spice bag and 4 to 5 whole sticks of cinnamon to syrup.
Slowly add peaches into the boiling syrup.
Cook until the fruit can be pierced with a broom straw.
Let stand in a covered kettle overnight.
The next day, pack into jars to 1/2 inch of top of jar.
Cover with syrup.
Put on tops tightly.
Process in water bath for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Steam the large cabbage leaves until limp.
Mix preceding ingredients; place in cabbage leaves and roll up.
Place in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over cabbage rolls. (Sprinkle with brown sugar if desired.)
Bake slowly for 1 to 2 hours.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.

Add remaining ingredients except rhubarb and beat 2 minutes. Add rhubarb. Place in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top of batter with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon mixed together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together adding pecans last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake in hot oven at 450° for ten minutes, turn oven to 350°, bake until a silver knife blade inserted in center of filling comes out clean.
This makes 2 pies.
This recipe can be doubled.
