title: all american dessert
directions: Stir 2 cups boiling water into each flavor of gelatin in separate bowls 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir 1 cup of cold water into each bowl.
Pour into separate pans. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Form desired shape and pan.
Bake for 1 hour, covered. Add cheese to top.
Bake 10 minutes more, uncovered.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in beer for 12 to 24 hours.
Grill brisket when brown.
Slice brisket and place in large pan.
Add onion, barbecue sauce and honey.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours on low heat. Serve hot, basted with sauce.

title: cherry delight
directions: Make graham cracker crust according to box.
Pack mixture into bottom of an oblong 9 x 11-inch pan, reserving 1/4 cup of mixture for later.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 400° for a meat loaf with a brown exterior. Grease a small baking pan.
Prepare bread crumbs (remove crust if desired).
Add minced onion and green pepper.
Break eggs into large bowl, beat slightly with fork.
Add meat; toss very slightly, until just blended.
Add bread crumbs, green pepper and onion.
Measure horseradish and next 4 ingredients.
Shape meat into an oval loaf in the bowl; then place in pan and smooth into shape.
Spread meat with 1/2 cup ketchup.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat salad puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, heat water and butter to rolling boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth and glossy.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about 25 minutes or until puffed, golden brown and dry.
Remove puffs to wire rack; cool away from draft.
Cut off tops of puffs; remove filaments of soft dough.
Fill each puff with slightly rounded teaspoonfuls meat salad.
Makes 6 dozen appetizers.

title: inexpensive sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Beat in salt, sugar and flavoring.
In a saucepan, heat the milk and butter to boiling point.
Add to the egg mixture.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add this to the mixture.
Pour very quickly into a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Bake immediately at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheddar potatoes
directions: Combine soup, paprika and pepper in a small bowl until well mixed.
Arrange potato slices overlapping in a greased 2 qt baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese. Cover and bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more or until potatoes are tender and golden.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar and let stand for 10 minutes, then add salt and bread flour, two cups at a time.
Mix thoroughly. Add more flour, two cups at a time, until dough comes away from sides of mixing bowl.
Grease bowl; place dough in greased bowl and cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise until the dough doubles in size.
If you don't use all the dough, punch residue down and put in refrigerator, covered with plastic.
Roll dough in 4-inch circles and dip in sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. In a large Ziploc bag, mix all ingredients together and shake well, making sure potatoes are coated.
Empty potatoes in a large pan.
Bake for about 40 minutes or until potatoes are done, stirring occasionally.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients well; fill egg halves; sprinkle with paprika.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and butter and allow to stand 20 minutes.
Add all ingredients to oatmeal mixture.
When cool, blend well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into Pam-sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350 for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple-banana punch bowl cake(low-fat, low sugar)
directions: Cook pudding mixed with sugar substitute, pineapple juice and milk until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool. Add pineapple and bananas.
Layer:
half of cake in bite size pieces, 1/2 of pudding mixture, half of cherries and half of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Mix all in a bottle with a cap.
Shake well before serving. Remove from refrigerator at least 1/2 hour before using as olive oil will solidify when cold.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt morsels with 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill.
Cut before becoming hard.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dump crushed pineapple and juice into cake pan.
Spread evenly.
Repeat with pie filling, cake mix and pecans.
Dot top evenly with bits of oleo.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Top each with topping.
Makes 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, pineapple and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil, simmering for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool and let set.

title: scallop corn
directions: Combine corn and all remaining ingredients except the cheese. Mix thoroughly and turn into greased 8-inch square baking dish. Top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, oil and 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured board 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in large greased bowl, turning to grease top of dough; cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Punch down, work into ball and cut in half.
Cut each half into 8 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into 20-inch rope and shape into pretzel.
Beat egg and brush on pretzels.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let rise 15 to 20 minutes until puffy.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 16.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix in bread cubes. Beat egg whites; fold into mixture.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: quick salsa
directions: Chop the tomato and onion.
Mix together. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, chill and serve.

title: pork chop hobos
directions: You will need 8 (12-inch) sections of aluminum foil.
Layout 2 sections of foil for each serving in a cross shape.
Place chop in center of foil.

title: congealed coca-cola salad
directions: Drain fruit from juice.
Heat juice and add jello to dissolve. Cool and add Cokes, fruit, nuts and crumbled cream cheese.
Serve on lettuce.

title: self-crust coconut custard pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend for 20 seconds. Pour into well-buttered 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° or until a knife comes out clean.

title: lemon and apricot supreme
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into tube pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Toothpick test for doneness. Cool in pan for 25 minutes or more.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Grate carrots and dice celery very small.
Cook with macaroni according to directions.
Carefully drain all the water off macaroni when finished cooking.
Add milk and dressing mix.
Use 3-quart buttered oven dish.
Layer macaroni, then cheese, covering top with cheese.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Beat and blend butter and sugars until creamy.
Add pudding mix, vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Add flour with soda and stir a cup at a time into mixture, then add chocolate chips and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: onion soup
directions: Microwave Cooking:
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, melt oleo on High.
Stir in onion rings.
Cook onions in butter on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in bouillon, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook on High for 5 minutes, reduce power to Medium and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve in bowls topped with croutons.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain any fat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Mix soup and milk, heat a little.
Pour over eggs.
Mix sausage and soup mixture, cheese and rice.
Crush cornflakes and mix with margarine.
Put half in bottom of pan.
Put sausage mixture on top.
Put rest of cornflakes mixture on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked fish loaf
directions: Flake or shred fish with two forks; combine with remaining ingredients except egg whites; fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased baking dish in pan of hot water in moderate oven one and one half hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sherried beef
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serves 5 to 8.
Serve with noodles.

title: barbecue salad
directions: This may be molded with any mixture of fresh vegetables.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Drop the tomatoes into a potful of simmering water for 10 seconds.
Take them out, pull off the skins and dice.
Combine everything in a small bowl or container.
Cover tightly and chill.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat,
rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into balls. Mix soup
and
water in pan.
Drop
meatballs
in pan. Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: capirotada (bread pudding)
directions: Toast bread in oven.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a saucepan with 1 1/2 quarts water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.

Reduce heat just enough to keep mixture warm. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the toast first, then the cheese, next the raisins, pecans, peanuts, coconut and sprinkles (using as much as desired or omitting if you do not like).
After each layer, pour some of the brown sugar mixture on top.
When complete, bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake 2 packages Mexican cornbread according to directions. Let cool.
Then crumble up into large bowl.
Add all ingredients listed; mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Yum.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve cool (room temperature).

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Brown chicken, then add all other ingredients.
Stir-fry until vegetables are at desired consistency.
Prepare rice to serve with this dish.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.

title: cheese rice krispers
directions: Let butter and cheese set at room temperature until soft. Grate cheese fine and mix with butter.
Sift red pepper and salt with flour and add to cheese and butter mixture.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: grilled caribbean chicken
directions: Combine mango, cucumber, cilantro, onion, pepper, lime juice, sugar and ginger.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Grill chicken breasts until done.
Top with salsa. (Low-fat.)

title: potato pie crustless
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Whip them with butter and milk. Season.
In bottom of casserole, put hamburg cooked or other meat if desired.
Add corn or other vegetables.
Add mashed potatoes. Cook in oven at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sandy's award winning raven chili
directions: In a large stock pot lightly saute onions and peppers in vegetable oil. Add remaining ingredients except ground beef. Simmer, on low for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often. (Stirring is important because the temperature at the bottom of the pot is hotter than the top.) Do not cover pot. Reduction of volume is important. we use a steam kettle which maintains temperature (165) throughout during simmering. A double boiler or large Bain Marie works, too. During the simmering process, brown ground beef in a skillet, chop and drain off excess grease or fat. Add cooked beef to stock pot and simmer another hour. It's ready to serve. Garnish with fresh chopped onion, grated Cheddar cheese and sour cream. Serve with large Fritos corn chips.

title: strawberry dream cake
directions: Dissolve jello in the thawed strawberries.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with miniature marshmallows and pour cake batter over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture over cake batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pizza popcorn
directions: Stir over 10 cups of popcorn.
Put in a jelly roll pan and put in a 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: high plain hash
directions: Warm oil and butter together in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add potatoes, onion, bell pepper and jalapeno and saute 10 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes, stirring mixture up from the bottom once every 6 or 7 minutes and patting it back down.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain English peas.
Add chopped eggs.
Mix pimento and mayonnaise.
Chill and serve in a bed of lettuce or shredded purple cabbage.

title: lemon crunch cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredient well.
Pat into 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan evenly.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and put on top of other layer.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Mix together with fork.
Knead; let rest.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine water, yeast and sugar.
Let proof for 5 minutes or until yeast begins to bubble.
Add salt, oil (if desired) and all but 1 cup of the flour.
Mix and knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Press dough with clean dry finger.
If it comes back clean and dough feels soft and springs back, it's ready to let rise.
If it's too sticky, add extra flour a tablespoon at a time until it does.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add jello and stir.
Add frozen raspberries.
Blend, breaking raspberries into chunks with a knife or large mixing spoon.
Chill about an hour or two.
Sets quickly.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Drain shrimp; rinse.
Cook onions and garlic in butter until soft.
Blend in flour; add water, tomato sauce and all ingredients, except shrimp.
Cover; simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover; continue cooking over low heat until mixture is reduced to about half.
Add shrimp; heat.
Serve over fluffy rice, garnished with sliced cooked eggs.

title: lattice top chicken(ready to bake in 10 minutes.)
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onions.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot on stove; simmer for 1 hour or use crock-pot and cook all day.
Freezes well.

title: sue's russian chicken
directions: Place chicken thighs in 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sausage and cheese rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Gradually add oil and milk.
Stir until well blended.
Divide into two parts and knead each a few minutes. Roll into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Spread sausage and top with cheese.
Refrigerate.
Slice thinly and bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and stem okra and pack in pint jars.
To each jar, add 2 cloves garlic, 1 pod red pepper and 1 stem dill.
Boil vinegar, salt and water and pour over okra.
Seal hot.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add oil, sugar and zucchini.
Mix well; add remaining.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: chocolate ginger bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°F.
Butter a 10x12-inch pan and dust with bread crumbs.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: In a bowl, combine chicken, onion, salt, lemon juice and celery.
Refrigerate several hours or until chilled.
At serving time, toss chicken mixture lightly with grapes, mayonnaise and all but a few orange segments and almonds.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: You will need 12 toothpicks to hold chicken together.

title: cole slaw salad
directions: Mix cabbage, carrot, pepper and onion.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt, oil, water and pepper.
Mix well.
May be kept in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Cook beans until soft.
Combine celery, pepper, parsley and scallions in large bowl.
Mix well vinegar and molasses in jar with lid on.
Pour over beans.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with radishes and tomatoes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening (can use fork).
Add sweet potatoes and enough milk to make a soft dough. Knead lightly.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits with cutter and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla, butter flavor, flour, buttermilk and salt.
Make paste of cocoa and food coloring; add to first batch.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl and add to batter.
Blend in baking powder.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Set aside white parts of eggs.
Mash yolks and blend with all remaining ingredients.
Use this mixture to fill the whites of the eggs.

title: italian eggplant balls
directions: Lightly
salt diced eggplant.
Steam with 4 tablespoons water in tightly covered saucepan (15 to 20 minutes).
Should be very soft.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Saute onion, celery
and garlic until very soft, but not brown.
Drain and cool eggplant in small colander.

title: byron's chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pizza baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed, drain and place in bottom of 8x8 baking pan.
Place mushrooms, black olives, and onions onto spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top.
Place cheese on top of sauce, then place pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Sift together last 4 ingredients.
Mix all and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their skins until tender.
Without peeling, slice potatoes thinly.
Peel and slice 1 red onion very thinly and separate into rings.
In a shallow dish place alternate layers of sliced potatoes and onion rings.
Salt and pepper each layer and sprinkle chopped parsley over each layer.

title: strawberry jubilee
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar; beat until very stiff.
Fold in pecans and crackers.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes in a 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Fold strawberries into Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Chill.
Freezes well.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk for 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt and sugar. Pour slowly over eggs.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in pan of hot water at 350° for about 50 minutes, or until knife inserted at center comes out clean.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours; stir often.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Defrost berries according to directions; drain.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and berries, beating until light. Mix flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Blend flour mixture into strawberry mixture, just until flour is moist.
Don't overmix.
Stir in nuts.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut meat in very small pieces and cook until done.
Remove bone and fat.
Put meat and broth in very large pot.
Add vegetables.
Cook until almost done; add tomato juice.
Let simmer for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients. If mixture is too dry add a little water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Part 1:
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Stir in oil, zucchini and flour.

title: sabine's cucumbers and cream
directions: Press cucumbers in drainer to remove excess liquid.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Add vinegar and enough cream to cover cucumbers. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill for several hours.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour, then add vinegar.
Cook over low flame.
When thick, add as much mayonnaise as you want.
This is real good for potato salad.

title: dream whip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan or 9 x 13-inch baking pan or cupcake pans.
Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and mix with electric mixer 4 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, cupcakes for 20 minutes.

title: linda's black walnut pound cake
directions: Take 2 tablespoons of flour and coat nuts; set aside.
Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time until blended.
Add sour cream.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and nuts and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn oven to 300° and bake for 1/2 hour. Check cake last 30 minutes.
May not take that long.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: lemon pie
directions: Melt butter; add 1 cup sugar and flour, blending well. Gradually add milk.
Heat over low heat until it begins to thicken.
Beat egg yolks; add lemon juice and rind.
Gradually add about 1 cup of hot milk mixture to eggs.
Combine the 2 mixtures and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked 9-inch pastry shell.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Mix in Ro-Tel tomatoes. Combine all hot ingredients.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes and green pepper in salad bowl.
Pour in meat and cheese mixture and toss. Top with taco and Doritos chips.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This is a moist cake.
Frost with Lemonade Frosting.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: chicken sour cream casserole
directions: Combine
margarine and stuffing
mix
and
blend
well. Spoon half of this into a
greased,
quart
casserole dish. Cover with chopped chicken (bite	size).	Combine
sour cream, soup, broth, salt and pepper.
Pour
over chicken and top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix flour, eggs and melted oleo, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Break up lettuce and place in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Break up cauliflower into very small bite-size pieces and arrange in pan on top of the lettuce.
Follow through with the remaining ingredients, creating a new layer with each ingredient.
Cover with topping.

title: olive potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 30 min. Once cheese starts to melt, stir.

title: talarini
directions: Mince and fry garlic, onion and bell pepper; add meat and fry until tender, using oil as needed to prevent burning.
Add about 2 cups tomatoes (use stewed).
Turn down low and cook about 10 minutes.
Boil noodles until tender.
Add corn to meat mixture. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour all into baking dish.
Add olives.
Grate cheese and stir together, leaving enough to sprinkle on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat with electric mixer the oil and eggs until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients, except apples.
Mix well. Stir in apples and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: walnut chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Stir well.
Pour over chicken mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill chicken mixture at least 2 hours.
Spoon 3/4 cup mixture on croissant.
Top with alfalfa sprouts and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: aloha sauce for fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Serve over a bowl of assorted fruits of your choice.

title: hot bags
directions: You will need one Reynolds Hot Bag.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken wings.
Mix mustard and honey together and brush on chicken. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In the bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered dish, put little pieces of chicken.
Mix the soup and 1/2 the broth; pour over chicken. Mix margarine, other 1/2 of broth and stuffing.
Pour on top of soup mixture.
Pour milk on top.
Cover and bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Mix and press into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs and butter.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix together melted butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 2 to 4.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and divide into 12 equal parts. Drop cabbage leaves in boiling water until pliable.
Drain and dry on paper towels. Wrap meat mixture in cabbage leaves and secure with toothpicks.
Combine sauce, vinegar, salt and Sweet-one.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake covered at 325° for 3 hours.
Baste occasionally during baking.
This makes 6 servings.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Combine flour, butter, brown sugar and nuts in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Crumble into 9 x 13-inch serving dish.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together in large bowl. Fold whipped cream into cheese mixture.
Spoon over crust.
Top with pie filling.
Freeze overnight.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil big pot of water with a little salt.
Meanwhile, add a little water to rice to let it swell.
Set aside.
Saute onion in oil.
Add a little garlic powder.
Core cabbage.
Put whole head of cabbage in boiling water or almost boiling to wilt leaves.
Put raw hamburger in bowl.
Add rice, salt and pepper (right much salt).
Mix.
Add onions (do not drain) and mix.
Pull leaves off cabbage with long fork and tongs while still in water (one at a time).
Can save the last ones because they are so small.

title: greek pita
directions: Clean, stem and chop spinach.
Beat eggs in large bowl and add spinach and cheeses.
Melt butter and begin by spreading in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place 2 strudel leaves on bottom and brush lightly with butter.
Keep going with 4 layers. Spread on half the filling, 4 more layers buttered, then the rest of filling.
Top with as many layers of dough as can fit.
Butter the top and sprinkle with wheat germ.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes, until golden.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Spread pie filling in buttered 8 x 8 dish. Sprinkle cake mix over the pie filling. Dot with margarine. Add nuts and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Simmer on low heat or in a crock-pot until thoroughly heated. Serve warm with orange slices.

title: crunchy pecan chicken
directions: Combine biscuit mix, seasonings and nuts; mix well.
Dip chicken in milk and coat with dry mixture.
Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour batter over top and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken livers and bacon(rumakis)
directions: Cut livers and bacon in half.
Soak 4 hours in enough soy sauce to cover; drain.
Slit sides of liver pieces, insert water chestnut, dip in brown sugar and wrap in bacon.
Fasten with toothpick and dip again in brown sugar.
Arrange on a wire rack over a shallow roasting pan.
Bake about 1/2 hour, turning a few times, in hot oven at 400°.
Can be served with dip of 1/2 part mayonnaise and 1/2 part mustard.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add water as needed.
Pour over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kulolo 2
directions: Mix together grated taro and grated coconut. Add water and coconut milk into sugar and mix well.
Pour into buttered cake pan and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: snow capped chocolate drops
directions: Combine brown sugar and melted butter.
Add eggs, soda and milk; mix well.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Add flour.
Stir in nut meats.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet; bake at 375°.
Remove from oven and put 1/2 marshmallow (cut in half) with sugar side up, on top of each cookie.
Return to oven to soften marshmallow (1 minute).
Remove and press down with spoon.
Cool on rack. Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion, garlic and oregano seasonings.
Remove from heat.
In large saucepan, heat Ragu sauce and add beef mix to sauce.
Cook noodles.
While these are cooking, mix Ricotta, parsley and egg together and grate Mozzarella cheese.
Layer as follows:
sauce, noodles, cheese and sauce.
Bake in 325° oven until bubbly and golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Cook dried beef with margarine in heavy skillet 5 minutes or until edges curl.
Sprinkle flour over beef and blend well. Remove from heat, slowly stir in milk, return to low heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thick.
Serve on hot crisp toast.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake as directed.
As soon as you remove cake from the oven, take a wooden spoon and poke holes in the top of the cake.
Next, pour Eagle Brand milk on top of the cake, then pour caramel topping on the cake.
Let cake cool.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Crush the Heath bars and sprinkle on top of the cake. Refrigerate.
Cake is supposed to be served cold.

title: razzberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup hot water.
Let set up until the consistency of egg whites.
Fold large dips of ice cream into the Jell-O with electric mixer until mixture is thick enough to eat with a spoon.
Enjoy!

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until mixture is melted and well blended.
Fill each patty shell half full with filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 15 tarts.

title: country ham casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain and chop. Cook spaghetti and drain.
In large casserole dish, heat Velveeta, milk and mayonnaise over low heat or microwave until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake 35-40 minutes or until hot at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° and let cool.
Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows.
Pour over pretzel layer.
Chill to set.
Mix boiling water with Jell-O.
Add sliced frozen strawberries.
When this mixture begins to set, pour on to the second layer and chill until firm.
Add nuts or pretzels to garnish.

title: creepy hands(great for halloween decoration)
directions: Place 3 pieces of candy corn into ends of each glove finger. Fill gloves tightly with popcorn. Close securely at wrist with ribbon. Place ring on one finger of each hand.

title: penuchi
directions: Combine milk and sugar.
Cook slowly, stirring only until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to 236° or when soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Add butter; cool slightly, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered pan (about 8 x 8-inch).

title: mama's chicken pot pie
directions: Put 1 teaspoon oil in frying pan.
Whiten chicken; do not cook it brown.
Add garlic and pepper as desired.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl.
Shred chicken and put into mixture, mixing well.
Pour into pie crust; preheat oven to 350° and put 2nd pie crust on top of your pie.
Cook until done, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with side salad.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in 3 quarts boiling water.
Drain and pour in greased casserole dish.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Add onion, celery and pepper.
Saute until tender.
Pour over spaghetti.
Mix well. Chop chicken and add, mixing well.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook in 400° oven until cheese is melted.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dump in bowl and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix in cherry pie filling last.

title: apple cheese filled rolls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix baking mix and sour cream until soft dough forms.
Turn dough onto cloth covered board dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll in baking mix to coat; knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Divide dough into halves.
Roll each half into 9-inch square with cloth covered rolling pin dusted with baking mix.
Cut into nine 3-inch squares.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Combine water, broth, mushroom, garlic, soy sauce and bouillon in 3 qt. Saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add pepper. Pour eggs in thin stream into soup, stirring constantly.
Cover and let stand 3 minutes. Sprinkle onions on top.

title: no bake rum balls
directions: Roll vanilla wafers very fine.
Add all of remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Coat hands with powdered sugar and roll dough into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Store in tightly sealed container.
These keep several weeks. Makes 40 small cookies.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spices and 1 cup water, simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer ground beef, sour cream, chips and 1 cup cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: symphony brownies
directions: Mix the brownie mix according to package directions. Spread half of brownies in a 9 x 13 pan. Put the 3 candy bars over brownie mixture. (The candy bars will fill the pan.) Spread the remaining batter over the candy. Bake according to package directions. Delicious!

title: pecan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Add flour, salt, oleo or cooking oil and nut meats. Bake in oblong pan or 8 x 8-inch pan for 25 minutes.

title: chewy noels
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch square pan over heat or while preheating oven.
Remove from heat as soon as it is melted.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine sugar, flour, soda and nuts.
Stir into beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture over butter.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and roll into confectioners sugar while still quite warm.

title: ham packages
directions: Prepare pie crust mix as directed.
On floured surface, roll to 1/16-inch thick.
Cut into 6 (7 or 7 1/2-inch) circles.
Thoroughly mix ham, soup, catsup, parsley, onion and mustard.
Spread about 1/3 cup mixture on 1/2 of each circle of dough.
Top with cheese half and a few egg slices.
Fold other half of dough over and seal edges with fork tines.
Prick top with fork.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° or until golden brown, about 40 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pink puff
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.

title: western style pork chops
directions: Combine the ingredients and marinate the chops for 1 hour or longer. Remove the chops from the marinade, reserving the marinade. Wipe the chops clean and dry. Brown the chops in a hot greased skillet. Heat the marinade with 1/2 cup water and pour over the chops. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until done. You can also bake the chops, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with rice.

title: caramel popcorn(candy)
directions: Put butter in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Microwave on High 1 minute. Stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Cover and microwave on High 4 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir until all is coated and no sugar mixture remains in dish.
Cook popcorn on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir well after each minute.
Remove from oven.
Spread in a lightly buttered 15 x 10-inch pan until cool.
Break into chunks.

title: beef cheese spread
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk and sour cream.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic salt.
Fold in beef.
Place in 8-inch pie plate. Brown pecans in butter and salt; sprinkle over mixture.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: spinach mushroom lasagna
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook onion and garlic in broth for 3 minutes until softened and beginning to color over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms and cook, stirring constantly, until they soften and release their juices.

title: eleanor's broccoli salad
directions: Chop tops and tender stalks of broccoli.
Steam with raisins just a few minutes.
Remove to a bowl and add onion.
Toss with sugar.
Add bacon and enough mayonnaise for a good consistency and again toss to combine.
Chill before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Spray large skillet with Pam and add 1 tablespoon margarine. Put in chicken.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and ginger.
Add celery pieces and cook until chicken is brown.
Combine water, brown sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Add pineapple and red pepper chunks. Pour over chicken.
Simmer for 15 or 20 minutes to combine flavors.
Serve over rice.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: *This has preservative qualities once baked.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes.
Core the inside, leaving a bowl to be stuffed.
Save tomato insides.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in narrow strips, brown slowly in oil about 15 minutes.
Add
onion
slices (separated in rings).	Season with salt and pepper.
Stir and cook 5 more minutes.
Add hot water. Cover
and simmer until meat is almost done;
about 30 minutes. Add
green	pepper	strips	and cook 10 more minutes.
Uncover. Add
mixture
of
cornstarch,
water
and
soy
sauce, stirring together.
Bring to a boil stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange and add remaining ingredients, except liquid.
Add liquid last and stir well.
Refrigerate until set.
Add more water if needed.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt to potato water. Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix alternately the flour, milk, potato water, yeast and sugar mixture. This should be a stiff dough. Stir.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Knead well. Roll into 1/4-inch thickness. Cut in strips.
Dip each piece in melted butter. Drop helter skelter in tube pan.
Let rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn upside down on plate.

title: breaded chops
directions: Combine the lemon juice, 1/3 cup olive oil, salt and pepper. Marinate chops in mixture for 2 hours.
Drain the chops and pat them dry on paper towels.

title: cheezy veggie soup
directions: Boil broth and add potatoes and onions.
Cook for 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add frozen vegetables and cook until tender.
Add soup and cheese, reduce heat and cook until cheese is melted and soup is thoroughly heated.
Top with bacon bits to serve (optional).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix soup, lemon juice, salt, pepper and mayonnaise; add remaining ingredients and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch baking dish 20 minutes at 425°, or until piping hot.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and boil eggplant with the onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/2 cup of mix and 1/2 cup hot water, or mix to suit your taste.
Add marshmallows if desired.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all and pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze for about 45 minutes.

title: caramel center candy
directions: Cook milk, sugars, syrup and margarine until soft ball stage; add vanilla and pecans.
Pour in buttered oblong pan to cool in refrigerator.
Chill.
Roll in balls and freeze on cookie sheet. Melt wax and chips in double boiler and dip.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine together well.
Good dip for any fresh fruit.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, hot water and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Cook to hard ball stage (250°) without stirring. Remove from heat.
Immediately beat 2 egg whites stiff (peaks stand straight up).
Pour hot syrup slowly over beaten whites, beating constantly at high speed (about 5 minutes).
Add the vanilla; beat until mixture forms soft peaks and begins to lose its gloss.
Add the walnuts, if desired.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream margarine, granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Add peanut butter; stir well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix to a stiff batter and add vanilla.
Form tiny balls with hands and press onto greased cookie sheet.
Press back of a fork to make waffle design. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
If desired, dough may be rolled, placed in refrigerator for several hours, then sliced.
Makes 4 dozen small cookies.

title: spicy chili
directions: Put everything in crock-pot and stir. Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and walnuts.
Add melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture and place remainder in 8-inch square pan.
Press firmly to form crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper.
Add to meat and brown.
Add chili powder, garlic salt, Ro-Tel, tomato soup, water and corn. Cook noodles.
Layer meat sauce, cheese and noodles.
Bake 35 minutes at 300° until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: italian soup
directions: Heat consomme, water and tomato sauce until boiling.
Add oregano, garlic salt and vegetables.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add pasta and cook until pasta is almost done.
Add meatballs; simmer until meatballs are hot and serve.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: coconut dreams
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and coconut, mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoons of mixture into balls.
Make an indentation in center of each and place a chocolate chip in each.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a double boiler, melt 1/3 cup milk and caramels.
Set aside.
Mix together 1/3 cup milk, melted oleo and cake mix.
Pour 1/2 of this cake batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 6 minutes. Remove from oven.
Pour the chocolate chips over the batter and cover with caramel mixture. Add remaining cake batter and bake 15 to 20 minutes. Cool 30 minutes before cutting.
Nuts may also be added with chips.

title: betty's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Place the tomatoes in a shallow serving dish.
In a bowl, mix oil, basil, vinegar and sugar; pour over tomatoes.
Cover; refrigerate for several hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cannelloni
directions: Cook shells or noodles; drain.
Mix all other ingredients except 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Stuff pasta and arrange in casserole dish.
Moisten bottom of casserole dish with thin layer of spaghetti sauce.
Top each shell with thin layer of sauce.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese on top.
Heat 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pear relish *
directions: Peel pears and grind; squeeze out juice.
Grind peppers and onions; mix with pears.
Put everything on stove in pan, bring to a boil and boil for 30 minutes.
Put in jars while hot and seal.

title: prize winning cauliflower supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
In large saucepan over medium-high heat, bring cauliflowerets and enough water to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain; with fork crush cauliflower into smaller pieces; do not puree.
In large bowl combine cauliflower, eggs, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella, Ricotta, salami and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs for topping.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese. Let it and margarine set overnight so it will be real soft. Mix cheese, flour, margarine, salt and paprika. Add Rice Krispies. Make it into small balls about the size of a marble and flatten with a fork. Bake on a greased baking sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: prairie fire bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Transfer mixture to a chafing dish.
Serve with taco chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: spicy tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large, heavy kettle.
Bring to boil and then simmer until as thick as desired.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Pour, boiling hot, into jars.
Leave 1/4-inch headspace and adjust lids.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Mix the egg yolk, 1/4 cup sugar and cream cheese until well blended.
Roll each slice of bread completely flat with a rolling pin.
Spread mixture lightly onto each slice.
Roll up like a jelly roll and set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup of sugar and cinnamon. Roll the bread slices into the melted butter and then into the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Spray a baking sheet with a nonstick spray and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add buttermilk, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Bake in electric frypan at 375° until brown on each side. Turn over once while cooking.

title: cornbread crawfish
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed.
Place half of cornbread mixture on bottom of pan.
Layer with ground meat, corn, crawfish and cheese.
Pour remaining cornbread over this.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned light fruit cake
directions: This recipe makes enough batter to fill two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or one 10-inch tube pan, or four 1-pound size coffee cans.

title: rave reviews lemon sheet cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat the cake mix and eggs until well blended. Fold in pie filling. Spread into a greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18-20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack.

title: best-ever cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine 2 1/4 cups of the flour and the yeast.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Mix well. Add enough mayo (Duke or Kraft real) to be very creamy.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white with water until foamy. Add pecan halves; stir until coated. Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Pour over pecans to coat. Place in foil-lined 10 x 16-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. Stir every 10 to 15 minutes. Stir to break up and cool.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Drain vegetables; place in bottom of a 2-quart (8 x 10-inch) baking dish.
Brown chicken on both sides; place chicken on top of vegetables.
Cover with sour cream.
Add cream of celery soup. Saute mushrooms and onions together.
Add dressing mix and onion soup.
Mix with 1 cup of water; stir well.
Cover chicken with dressing mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4. Serve with hot rolls and tossed salad.

title: possum grape dumplings(walakshi choctaw)
directions: Possum grapes ripen in the fall throughout Indian country.
If the housewife doesn't have wild grapes, store bought grapes may be used or unsweetened grape juice.
Prepare juice by adding 1/2 cup of sugar to 2 1/2 cups of grape juice.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil and add a dash of lemon juice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil cornstarch, Karo, sugar and water until thick.
Pour over strawberries placed in baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: garden salad
directions: Wash and drain the lettuce and combine all other ingredients. Add dressing of choice and toss to coat.

title: cranberry-orange salad
directions: Section oranges; dice finely and drain.
Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Stir cranberry sauce until smooth; blend into gelatin with orange rind.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in diced orange and nuts.
Chill.

title: pickled cauliflower
directions: Dissolve salt in water enough to cover vegetables, and let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain them.
Heat vinegar with mustard until it boils.
Add the vegetables and boil for about 15 minutes or until fork can be thrusted through cauliflower.

title: fried fish (diet)
directions: Mix together the flakes, oil and seasonings.
Coat both sides of fish.
Place on ungreased nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
May use for chicken or pork chops, etc.

title: exciting pasta
directions: Boil fettucini as directed on package; drain. In a pan, heat oleo and picante sauce; add cheese. Remove from heat when oleo melts. Add the sour cream and salt. Add the still warm fettucini and mix in.

title: frozen chocolate cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press on bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: country style corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
Pour mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese; return to oven and bake 20 more minutes.

title: baked oysters
directions: Heat together in a casserole the milk and butter until butter is melted.
Drain the oysters.
Remove casserole from oven and add alternate layers of cracker crumbs and oysters to milk.
Add more crumbs if needed but do not overload.
Keep it slightly juicy. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tofu-stuffed zucchini(low-fat dish)
directions: Wrap the tofu in absorbent toweling.
Place a heavy weight on top for 10 minutes to squeeze out the excess moisture.
Wash thoroughly and trim ends from zucchini.
Slice zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out the pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop the zucchini pulp and reserve for later use.
Saute the onion and garlic in the vegetable oil until softened.
Add the chopped zucchini pulp and cook until softened (about 10 minutes).

title: mary lee's sugared pecans
directions: Heat nuts in oven to slightly brown; stir often.
Cool.
Cook sugar, water, cinnamon and salt to a soft ball stage.
Do not stir. Add vanilla and nuts; stir until mixture gets creamy and pour on buttered pan.
Let harden and they pop apart.

title: perkins and packwoods favorite cheesecake
directions: Combine melted margarine and crushed graham crackers to form crust.
Press into bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill. Boil water and dissolve jello. Stir well and set aside to cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions, gradually add to the cream cheese mixture.
Stir in cooled jello.
Slowly pour into chilled crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill for approximately 6 hours, until set.

title: bacon-cheese bread
directions: Peel all crust off of the French bread.
Cut bread into 8 or 10 thick slices diagonally.
In a saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons margarine and add mustard, onions and poppy seed.
Spoon mixture between slices.
Place 1 slice of cheese between each bread piece. Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted margarine over loaf.
Arrange 1 to 2 slices bacon over each piece.
Bake on greased foil at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep ovenproof dish.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, milk and vanilla flavoring (almond is good with cherries) to make a batter (pancake consistency).
Pour over melted margarine.
Gently pour in fruit - juice and all.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes until top is browned.

title: peanut butter swirl(for ice cream)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Remove from heat. Add the peanut butter.
Beat until smooth with beater.
Serve with ice cream.

title: quick company chicken
directions: Place breasts
in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole, slice of Swiss cheese on each breast.
Sprinkle with mushrooms.
Mix soup with
wine	and pour over chicken.	Sprinkle herbed bread dressing over
contents
and
drizzle
melted
butter over the dressing. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: lemon dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix together butter, flour and chopped pecans. Place in 9 x 13 pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: sunburst ice cream parfait
directions: Scoop ice cream into 4 balls, using 1/2 cup ice cream
for each.
Roll balls in sunflower nuts.
Hold in freezer until ready to serve.
Place ice cream balls into serving dish.
Drizzle each with 2 tablespoons honey to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles and rinse.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of a 15x10x2-inch baking dish with non-stick spray.
Spread 3/4 cup of lasagna sauce on bottom of dish.

title: potato dressing
directions: Chop celery and
onion fine.
Simmer in butter until soft. Beat eggs.
Mix all together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: best-ever meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and bread.
Let stand a few minutes.
Stir in onion, carrot, cheese, herbs and seasonings. Add meat; mix well.
In shallow baking pan, shape meat mixture into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Mix soda and buttermilk, then dissolve sugar.
Use a big saucepan and boil slowly to soft ball stage.
Mixture turns brown as it cooks, but needs stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add flavorings, oleo and pecans.
Stir until it begins to look like it is ready to cream.
Drop in small cakes on wax paper.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook squash in salted water about 5 minutes and drain.
Butter medium size baking dish lightly.
Alternate layers of squash, soup (undiluted), almonds, pimento and dot with butter.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake in 375° oven, depends on your stove (approximately 20 minutes).
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In saucepan, combine syrup, sugar and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil gently, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir and cool slightly. Place pecans in bottom of pie shell.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients in bowl and set aside.
Brown pie crust.
Remove crust from oven and add mixed ingredients.
Put back in oven and bake for 8 minutes on 350°.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove cabbage core with sharp knife and scald in hot water. Remove a few leaves at a time and trim thick ridge from back of leaves to make it easier for rolling.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine onion with the meat, rice, egg and seasonings and mix well.

title: ham & cheese ribbons
directions: Cut each slice ham into 4 (1-inch) wide strips.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Sift these ingredients together.
When ready, use 1/3 cup of mix with 1 cup boiling water.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft- drain - mash until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy. Put in 9x13 inch pan. Cover and place in refrigerator. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes or until heated through, when ready to use.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
In saucepan simmer Ranch Style beans and picante sauce.
Bread lettuce up into bite size pieces. Dice tomatoes, onion and avocado.
Add to lettuce.
Add bean mixture and toss together.
When ready to serve, add cheese, Fritos and Catalina dressing.
Serve.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallow cream.
Line 9 x 13 pan with waxed paper.
OTHERWISE THE CAKE WILL STICK TO PAN AND COME APART. Pour batter into pan.
Batter will be thick.
Spread to edges and corners.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cake from pan. Cover hot cake with marshmallow cream.
Swirl frosting over cake with knife.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook onions and parsley in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper, lemon peel and sour cream.
Stir in beans and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Buttered crumbs or grated almonds may be used as a topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef tacos
directions: Heat peanut oil in skillet over medium heat; add ground beef and brown, stirring to break up meat.
Add onion and garlic; continue cooking until onion is tender.
Mix in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Spoon beef mixture into prepared taco shells.
Top with cheese and lettuce.
Makes 12 tacos.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Grill about 20 pieces of chicken on grill.
Put chicken into sauce and simmer on top of stove for about 2 hours.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Add flour and salt. Stir in juice. Pour in crust. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes two 10-inch pies.

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Rinse the chicken wings in cold water.
Towel excess water off.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, mix remaining ingredients. Add chicken wings and turn to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate. Let marinate for 1 to 8 hours, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake chicken in marinade, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.
Serve warm or cold.
(If it's a nice day, barbecue on the grill.)
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: marvelous meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil, thoroughly.
Form into 1 inch meatballs.
Heat oil in nonstick pan.
Brown (don't cook) meatballs on all sides.
Add to your favorite sauce and let them cook in the sauce.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix salt, baking powder, flour, sugar and milk in bowl.
Pour over margarine.
Add fruit (peaches, blackberries, cherries, apples or strawberries).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix well; store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart.

title: tex-mex chili
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook beef and onions with garlic, chili powder, cumin and pepper until beef is browned and onions are tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat. Stir in flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in V-8 juice.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Reduce heat to low; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans; simmer 15 minutes more, stirring occasionally.

title: cherry banana cobbler
directions: Peel bananas and cut into thirds.
Place into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Stir lemon juice into pie filling. Spoon over bananas.
Cook, uncovered, in countertop microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir to coat bananas.
Sprinkle crumbs atop. Microcook, uncovered, about 2 minutes, or until heated through. Serve with ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: angel delight
directions: Make cake; cool and rip into pieces.
Make pudding and stir until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fill a bowl with 1/3 cake pieces. Top with 1/3 pudding and 1/2 strawberries.
Layer again.
Slice kiwi.
Do one more layer and layer it with the fanciest berries and kiwi.
Put dollop of Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
This is so delicious.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Top with melted butter. Cover with foil and refrigerate at least 1 hour (the longer, the better).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: frosted green bean salad
directions: Marinate several hours or overnight the green beans, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and onion.
Combine eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Add sugar, if desired.
Add bacon. Chill.

title: laura black's cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread butter on loaf.
Combine the rest of ingredients and spread.
Split loaf lengthwise, then cut each half into 8 slices.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
(Don't let brown.)

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Place tomatoes, tomato paste, orzo and chopped onion in 2 quarts of boiling water. Simmer 20 minutes, covered. Add hamburg meat, bouillon cubes and Veg-All. Simmer 1/2 hour. Serve with fresh bread for a delicious wintry night dinner!

title: pepper corn
directions: Fry bacon and onion together.
Drain off half the fat.
Add corn, tomatoes, green pepper and salt.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: delicious dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, tomato soup and dry jello.
Mix well.
Then add onion, peppers and mayonnaise.
Serve with chips.
This keeps real well.

title: tomato relish
directions: Chop
peppers,
onions
and tomatoes; add spices, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover with vinegar. Cook until thick.

title: easy bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar,
mustard
seed, turmeric and celery seed. Bring
to rolling
boil.
Add
drained
cucumbers
and onions. Return to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and pack in sterile jars.
They will seal themselves.
Makes 5 pints.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy with fork or hand beater.
Then add sugar, salt and milk; mixing thoroughly in a large bowl.
Next, stir in flour and baking powder, making sure that there are no flour or sugar clumps left in the batter.
(Hint: Sift sugar, flour and baking powder before adding to mixture.)

title: bacon cheese appetizers
directions: Line a microwave-safe baking dish with double layer of paper toweling.
Pace bacon slices on dish.
Cover with paper toweling. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.

title: olde english pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 1 hour at 275°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: gyros(greek delight)
directions: Mix lamb, water, lemon juice, salt, cumin, oregano, pepper, garlic and onion.
Shape into 4 thin patties.
Cook patties in oil over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes, turning frequently, until done.
Split each bread halfway around with knife and separate to form pocket.
Place patty in each pocket.
Top with shredded lettuce.
Mix yogurt, mint and sugar; stir in cucumber.
Spoon onto lettuce and top with tomato.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese mixture on top of bread.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Chop cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, sprouts and green onion.
Sprinkle on top of cream cheese.
Cut and enjoy.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, add sugar, salt, oil and flour. Stir and let rest 5 minutes.
Will make enough for a small cookie sheet.
Spray hands with Pam and spread.
Add toppings as you desire.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: oatmeal breakfast "treat"
directions: Bring water, salt and butter to a boil.
Add oatmeal, cinnamon, flavoring, sugar and milk together.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: frosty orange nog
directions: Place ingredients in blender; cover and whirl until smooth.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Good served with baked ham.

title: play dough
directions: First, use care to select one, not too young, but tender and healthy.
Make your selection carefully and let it be final; otherwise, they will not keep.
Do not pickle him or put him in hot water.
This makes him sour.
Prepare as follows:
sweeten with smiles accordingly.
The sour, bitter kind are improved by a pinch of salt of common sense.
Spice with patience.
Wrap well with charity.
Preserve over a good fire of steady devotion. Serve with peaches and cream.
The poorest variety may be improved by this process and kept for years in any climate.

title: shaver ranch style baked beans
directions: Brown meat and drain. Stir in soup mix, beans, catsup, water, mustard and vinegar.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fudge
directions: Melt the cheese and margarine on low.
Sift sugar and cocoa into large bowl.
Pour cheese and margarine into this and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Use at least two cups but more if you like.
Cool and cut. It makes 7 1/2 lbs.
Put in cookie sheet.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients. Sprinkle with crushed bread crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peach pie
directions: Place sliced peaches in unbaked pie shell. Cream together sugar, flour and butter. Add egg and vanilla. After blended together, spread mixture over peaches. Bake at 375 degrees for 1/2 hour, then bake at 300 degrees for 1/2 hour. Very good!

title: mother jessie's biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse corn meal.
Add buttermilk. Mix well.
With floured hands on floured surface, shape dough. Roll out to approximately 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into circles with floured biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for about 10 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Boil pasta.
After pasta is boiled (oil and salt in water) until soft, remove and drain water.
Mix all ingredients together. Once mixed, place in pan.
Then place in oven at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 15 minutes.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill a while.
Put cherry pie filling on top and chill again.

title: easy and tasty moist cake
directions: Use a metal 8 1/2 x 11 baking pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix evenly into the baking pan.
DO NOT use anything to grease the pan.
Break the eggs into the dry cake mix in the baking pan.
Add the water and cooking oil and stir with a regular fork just until the dry mix is absorbed.
There will be some small lumps in the batter and this is okay.
Using a tablespoon, drop the pie filling evenly into the batter.
Use a regular table knife to create a marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the cake's center appears to be clean.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream and egg whites with a fork until blended.
May still be a little crumbly.
Spread into jellyroll pan.
(A butter knife dipped into water works great for spreading dough.)
Distribute pie cherries evenly over entire batter and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Use liquid from clams to soften cream cheese to desired consistency.
Use Worcestershire and Tabasco to season to taste. Serve with Fritos.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: Boil chicken until tender and cut in small pieces.
Cook noodles in chicken broth until tender.
Cook butter, pepper, pimentos and mushrooms in a skillet until tender.
Add Worcestershire and Tabasco sauce.
Combine chicken, noodles, pepper mixture and English peas with enough broth for the right consistency and bring to a boil.
This should not be soupy, but moist.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: Approximately 60 minutes.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Grease bottom only of loaf pan.
Combine ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes; turn out onto wire rack and cool completely.

title: monkey bread or bubble bread
directions: Cube bread and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over cubes.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; add olive oil.
Lightly brown minced garlic.
Add clam juice, clams, parsley flakes, basil, red pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil, let simmer about 10 minutes.
Thicken with approximately 1 tablespoon cornstarch; simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Serve over linguine.

title: foccacio pizza crust
directions: Put 2 cups tepid water in bowl.
Add yeast and let dissolve. Add 3 cups flour, sugar, salt, olive oil and vegetable oil.
Beat with mixer until dough pulls away from bowl.
Then add 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat to a glossy glow.
Allow dough to rise for about an hour.
Punch dough down, cover and allow to rise again.
Knead dough with hands.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Sift again with soda and salt.
Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add buttermilk and flour.
Add chopped fruits and chopped nuts.
Chill dough for several hours.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at moderate heat (350°) for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Put dry ingredients in a bag. Add chicken and shake until coated. Spray baking pan with nonstick oil and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Measure cereal; crush to 3/4 cup.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Measure margarine and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and orange peel.
Beat well.
Stir in orange juice.
Add dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

title: parisian lemon cake
directions: Cream butter, 1 cup of the sugar and lemon peel until consistency is smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and juice of 1 1/2 lemons.
Sift together the flour and baking powder; fold gently into butter.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Season tenderloin with spices; let set at room temperature for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° with meat thermometer (140° rare, 150° medium rare, 165° to 170° well).
Cool slightly; slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Never cook without a thermometer.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Combine fresh spinach, water chestnuts, eggs, bean sprouts, bacon and onion in medium bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; stir until sugar is dissolved, then pour over spinach when ready to serve.

title: sugarless cranberry sauce
directions: Combine cranberries and water in 3 quart casserole.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on high 11-13 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Stir in sweetener.
Let stand covered 10 minutes.
Sauce will thicken as it cools.
Store in fridge.

title: honey chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; place chicken in it.
Mix rest of ingredients; pour over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until tender.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cut chicken breasts into about 1-inch chunks (I use a large electric skillet). Place all meat in pan and cook until done, try not to brown.

Remove from pan. Place butter and onion; simmer until tender. Add apple and curry powder; simmer until tender. Add apple and curry powder; simmer about 5 to 10 minutes. Add bouillon. Blend cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water; add to skillet. Stirring, add milk. Add chicken; stir and simmer about 5 minutes until hot.
Serve over rice. We prefer a mix of brown and wild or just brown.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan, combine oil, onion, bell pepper and chilies.
Stir over high heat until onion is soft, 6 to 8 minutes. Add broth, tarragon and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Cut corn kernels off cob and simmer until corn is hot, about 5 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Serve hot or cold.
Garnish with tarragon sprigs.

title: meringue for pies
directions: Beat 4 egg whites until stiff.
Add Marshmallow Creme.

title: steak and wine
directions: Remove any fat from meat, then cut into serving slices.
Line a roaster pan with the steak, salt and pepper.
Spread the cream of mushroom soup on top of meat.
Sprinkle flour over soup.
Pour wine over flour.
Cover roaster and put into oven at 400° for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until the meat is tender.
Makes its own gravy.

title: lime sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large container.
Add cold water and sherbet; stir until sherbet is almost melted.
Add drained pineapple, marshmallows and chopped pecans.
Pour into 12 x 18-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into serving portions. Yields 50 servings.

title: hamburger meat and mushroom soup dish
directions: Saute ground meat, bell pepper, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Then add cream mushroom soup and tomatoes. May add little water and simmer. Cook spaghetti or macaroni, then put into your sauce.

title: dough for chicken pie
directions: Knead and roll thin.
Cut strips 1-inch wide. Drop small pieces into boiling chicken.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into crust.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: chili potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until tender.
Add skim milk just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: microwave broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1-quart covered casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; turn dish and heat 1 minute more.
Drain.
Add onion; stir gently.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add cheese and rice; stir to blend.
Adjust seasoning.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cuban black bean soup
directions: Add fresh water to beans.
Simmer for 5 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for another 2 hours.

title: german applesauce meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a small casserole or a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: pazetti(will feed 25)
directions: After boiling noodles, layer in bottom of pan.
Cook next 4 ingredients together, then layer on top of noodles.
Put cheese on top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, until golden and bubbly at 350°.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and buttermilk; beat just until blended.
Gradually add melted butter, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake in waffle iron.

title: krispie cheese wafers
directions: Grate cheese and cream with oleo. Sift dry ingredients and add to cheese mixture.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Let dough stand in refrigerator overnight.
Roll into balls and flatten into small wafers with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about six dozen.

title: dublin coddle(codal ath cliathach)
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes. Slice onions. Place ingredients in a saucepan and cook until hot, but not mushy.
Serve hot.

title: linda's fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer:
lettuce on bottom, cauliflower, chopped red onions. Repeat layers as many times as you want.
Top with mayonnaise or Ranch dressing and fried bacon and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: macaroni 'n beef
directions: At Camp:
Cook macaroni as directed on package for skillet method.
Drain.
Blend 1 1/2 cups water, soup mix, cheese sauce mix and dried beef.
Bring to a boil and simmer a few minutes. Add more water if necessary.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: lovin sweetcakes
directions: Prepare cake batter as directed on package. Stir in dry powdered Jell-O until well mixed. Line 24 medium muffin pan cups with paper liners. Pour batter evenly into cups, filling each cup half full. Bake as directed on box for cupcakes. Cool completely. Spread 2 tablespoons whipped topping on each cupcake. Sprinkle with the sprinkles. Use sprinkles for any holiday.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Scoop out insides of potatoes into a large bowl.
Mix in butter and salt, pepper.
Then add remaining ingredients, saving some cheese and onions to go on top.
Bake at 400 degrees, stirring occasionally, until bubbly.
Then put cheese and onions on top, let melt and serve!

title: heath bits peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Beat shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl until well blended. Add egg. Beat just until blended. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually beat into peanut butter mixture. Stir in 1 cup Heath bits. Reserve remainder for topping. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Top each with reserved Heath bits. Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until set. DO NOT OVERBAKE. Cool 2 minutes. Remove to wire racks. Cool completely.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham quiche
directions: Melt butter.
Put mayonnaise, flour, eggs, milk and butter in blender and blend well.
Bake pie shell at 400° for 3 minutes. Remove from oven, prick with fork and bake 5 minutes longer.
Stir ham and cheese into blender mixture but do not blend.
Bake in pie shell at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes for deep shell or 30 to 40 minutes for regular shell.

title: company pot roast
directions: In large Dutch oven over medium heat, brown roast in corn oil. Add the next 8 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for at least 2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add green beans and whole onions.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until beans and onion are tender-crisp.
Remove roast to a large platter, arrange vegetables around the roast.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut each squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and fibers. Pare and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in ungreased 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Mix together the margarine, brown sugar, flour, salt and mace.
Sprinkle half of sugar mixture on squash slices.
Top with apples which have been cored and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 60 to 80 minutes at 350° until the squash is tender.

title: baked chicken breasts with sour cream
directions: Mix together sour cream with lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, salt, paprika and garlic salt.
Dip chicken breasts in sour cream mixture and roll in stuffing mix.
Arrange in a shallow, greased baking dish.
Brush with melted butter.
Place, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: easy fruit delight
directions: Combine together first
four ingredients in a bowl and sprinkle walnuts on top.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine ingredients and roll in small balls.
Dip in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together; add milk and bring to a boil in a heavy sauce pan.
Pour some of the hot liquid into egg yolks beating as you do so.
Return all of it to the sauce pan and mix well as you are adding it.
Cook as you stir until it begins to bubble.

title: strawberry cheese ring
directions: Combine cheese, onion, pepper and mayonnaise.
