Blend ingredients well.
Stir in pecans until well blended.
Shape mixture into a ring on a plate, leaving a hole in center.
You can line a jello mold or tube cake pan with wax paper and press firmly to mold.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Just before serving, fill hole with strawberry preserves.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Very tasty.

title: swiss cheese ball
directions: Mix together using enough mayonnaise to hold together. Form into a ball and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and beat well.
Place pan on stove on medium heat and bring to a boil; stir.
In an iron skillet, melt one cup of sugar until "good and dark."
Add to other ingredients, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Bake in two unbaked pie shells at 350° until done.
Beat the four egg whites until stiff, adding about 1/4 cup sugar.
Put on pies and brown.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: First Layer:
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread nuts over butter. Cover with coconut.

title: blueberry crumble
directions: Put blueberries and sweetener in small baking dish.
Mix together next 3 ingredients.
Stir in margarine; pour dry ingredients over berries.
Microwave on High power for 1 minute and 20 seconds.
Makes one serving.

title: boiled coconut icing
directions: Boil until it isn't too runny.
Put spoonful on saucer to check.
If it doesn't run it is ready.

title: spanish style scrambled eggs(lo-fat)
directions: In nonstick skillet, heat the oil on medium-high. Add the onion and tomato. Saute until the onion is soft (about 1 to 2 minutes).
Reduce heat to low.
In a bowl, combine the egg whites, picante and pepper. Beat until frothy. Add to skillet, cooking on low heat. Add the cilantro and stir until the eggs are set fully.
You could use the equivalent of 6 eggs or egg substitute, if you wish.
Serves 3.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, water, and vinegar.
Heat to boiling. Add cream of tartar.
Boil to soft crack stage (275° to 280°). Remove from heat.
Add butter, baking soda, and vanilla.
Pour over pop corn.
Form into balls.

title: harvest rice
directions: Saute carrots in butter for 5 minutes or until tender-crisp. Add 1 1/4 cups water, juices, brown sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, cinnamon and raisins.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in green onion and apples.
Cook until heated through.
Turn into serving dish.
Top with sesame seed.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: homestyle short ribs(slo-cooker pot)
directions: Brown ribs well.
Place potatoes, carrots and onion in slow cooking pot.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place ribs in cooker and pour mixture over them.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender.

title: peanut butter cup tassies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo, peanut butter, vanilla and egg together. Then add flour salt and soda.
Roll into about 36 balls.
Put balls in small tassie pans.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Put a peanut butter cup in the center as soon as they come out of the oven.
Press down into center (the cookie will come up around sides).
Let them cool in pans completely before removing.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Put in graham cracker pie shell and chill.

title: pea salad
directions: Thaw peas and pearl onions in hot water (about 10 minutes). Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate about 2 hours prior to serving.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick of butter. Press in bottom of 9x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Cream the sugar, cream cheese and 1 stick butter.
Add
2 eggs and nuts.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: batter
directions: In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add water and egg. Stir until smooth.
Pour 1 quart (about) corn oil into large skillet to depth of 1/2-inch, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat to 375°.
Dip 4 cups cut-up vegetables, such as zucchini, carrots, onion and mushrooms, or 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into 1-inch cubes, a few at a time, into batter.
Stir batter occasionally.
Carefully add vegetables or chicken to hot oil, a few pieces at a time.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning once, until golden brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels. Serves 4 to 6.

title: becky swaim's almond tea
directions: Simmer sugar, water and lemon juice for 5 minutes and cool. Mix well with remaining ingredients and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon. Remove from freezer 5 hours before serving; it will be slushy consistency.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and toss with broccoli mixture.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Enough potatoes to fill any size baking dish you want to use. Alternate layers of potatoes and ham.
Cover with medium white sauce.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: summer delight
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan until done.
Let cool.
Mix jello pudding, sugar, milk and cream cheese until thick.
Spread on top of cool cake.
Top with drained pineapple, then Cool Whip, then nuts.
Refrigerate.
Can be made a couple of days ahead if need be.

title: dill weed nibbles
directions: In large container, empty the oyster crackers and place the oil on top.
Stir with a wooden spoon to coat the crackers and let stand for about 1/2 hour (stirring in between).
Mix dry ingredients together and toss over the crackers, stirring 3 or 4 times.
You may store the crackers in Ziploc bags as the crackers stay fresh or put in the freezer for future use.
(Once you start munching these, there's usually not any leftovers!
Great for parties!)

title: dumplings
directions: Add enough flour to remaining ingredients to make thick, like cookie dough.
Drop by teaspoons into boiling chicken broth or roll out on floured board and cut into strips.
Drop in chicken broth; cook about 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mash pumpkin; add brown sugar and eggs.
Mix milk to flour. Add rest of ingredients.
Brown butter and put on top of pies before baking them.
This makes 3 pies.
Bake in a 350° oven until thick when you shake it or until center is set.

title: peanut butter roll(candy)
directions: Boil sugar, water and
syrup together until a hard boil when tried in cold
water.
Beat
egg whites stiff.
Let syrup cool a little, then
pour
slowly
over the beaten egg whites. Add vanilla.
Beat until stiff
enough to roll out or it won't stick to fingers when
touched.
Roll out using powdered sugar as you would flour.
Spread
with
peanut butter that has been warmed a little, then roll
up
as
a jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper;
put in refrigerator overnight, then slice and eat it.

title: chilled raspberry soup
directions: Combine frozen raspberries, water, 1/2 cup red wine, cinnamon and sugar in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce to simmer for 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix arrowroot and the 1 1/2 tablespoons of red wine.
Stir into a simmering soup.
Add a pinch of salt.
Remove from heat.
Let cool and put into a different container.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with fresh raspberries and a dollop of yogurt on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix into partially thawed potatoes.
Pour mixture into greased casserole.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: banana carrot spice cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, allspice and set aside.
Combine sugar, oil and vanilla in a bowl and beat until well blended.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour mixture alternately with the mashed bananas at low speed.
Stir in shredded carrots and walnuts, mixing thoroughly.
Turn into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until it tests done.

title: quick carbonara
directions: Brown bacon in frypan; drain.
Crumble and reserve bacon; pour off fat.
Add oil, butter, garlic and ham to pan; saute lightly. Add spaghetti, bacon, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; stir well. Turn off heat.
Pour eggs over and quickly toss to coat spaghetti evenly.
Decorate with parsley.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together margarine and peanut butter.
Gradually add granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Then add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls (about 1-inch).
Roll balls in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and top each cookie with Hershey Kiss, pressing down so cookie cracks around the edge.
Return to oven.
Bake about 2 to 5 minutes longer (be careful they don't get too brown).

title: frito pie
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, crush 1/2 bag Fritos and layer on bottom of pan.
Slice tamales and put on top of Fritos. Put heated chili on top of tamales.
Sprinkle desired amount of remaining Fritos on top of that.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes or until heated and cheese melts in 350° oven.
Also good with a little sour cream put on top before you eat it.

title: beef jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Dry 8 to 12 hours.

title: diabetic's apple sugarless pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and apple juice concentrate.
Cook, and stir until it begins to clear.
Stir in apples and spices.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake 35-40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and boil in small amount of water until tender. Drain thoroughly, then mash.
Add all ingredients, except 1/2 of butter. Salt and pepper may be adjusted to taste.

Pour squash in a shallow lightly greased baking dish. Pour melted butter over top and sprinkle with additional crushed saltines, if desired. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until browned on top, depending on size of pan it may be done earlier.
Start checking at about 30 minutes.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, shortening, eggs and milk together well.
Press into bottom of 10-inch cake pan.
Add pie filling. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Cook large package of mixed vegetables.
Add chicken soup, chicken broth and chicken which has been torn in bite size pieces. Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Mix well and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine crumbs and margarine; mix well.
Press 8 cups of crumb mixture on bottom of 18 x 26-inch pan.
Pour the Eagle Brand condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
In a bowl, combine chips, coconut and nuts.
Sprinkle 5 cups of chip mixture over Eagle Brand milk; press down gently. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans, onion, cheese, dressing, tomatoes and cucumbers. Chill for several hours.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix broccoli, cottage cheese, eggs, onion and corn bread mix.
Pour over melted butter in the pan. Lightly blend.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean bake
directions: Drain canned beans.
Combine beans, mushroom soup and lemon juice.
Turn
mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with onions and continue baking about 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: party mix
directions: Combine dressing and dill weed in large bowl.
Add cereal, oyster crackers and pretzels, tossing well.
Drizzle oil over mixture; stir well.
Place mixture in a large paper bag and close. Let stand for 2 hours, shaking bag occasionally.
Store in airtight container.

title: banana cake
directions: In
lavae
mixing bowl cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and
lemon juice.
Beat well.
Add mashed bananas.
Sift together flour, mace, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Fold
in
nuts.
Bake
in
Bundt
pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until
cake
tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn on serving plate and top with lemon or vanilla glaze.

title: muffin tin meat loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except ketchup, mixing lightly but thoroughly.Spoon approximately 1/3 cup beef mixture into each of 12 muffin cups and press lightly to fill cups. Spread ketchup over tops. Bake 20 minutes or until centers are no longer pink. Remove meat loaves from pan. Serve with mashed potatoes, if desired. Serves 6.

title: no fail pie crust or tart shells
directions: Whip Crisco, milk and water until the consistency of whip cream.
Mix in 2 cups flour and salt.
Dough will be real flexable.
Flour board and roll out dough.
Great for fried pies.

title: creole green beans
directions: Cook onion in oil until soft.
Add chili sauce, salt and drained green beans.
Cook only until thoroughly heated, stirring often.

title: orange-mustard chicken
directions: Season chicken breast with ginger.
Brown in frypan with Pam. Add to chicken the juice of orange and Dijon mustard.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: peach waldorf salad
directions: Wash, peel and cut in half peaches.
Remove pit.
Dice.
In large bowl combine the peaches, celery and pecans.
Refrigerate, covered, until well chilled.
Will take about 1 hour.
Just before serving, whip cream in medium bowl until stiff.
Combine sugar and mayonnaise.
Gently fold into whipped cream to combine.
Then fold into the chilled peach-celery mixture.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat
directions: Put sugar on it.
Then put it in a pot.
Then it's meat.

title: do-ahead slaw
directions: Toss cabbage, sugar, onion, olives and green pepper in a large bowl; set aside.

title: heath bar squares
directions: Combine crushed wafers and melted butter.
Press into bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Soften cream cheese. Stir in mushroom stems (finely chopped), walnuts, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce.
Fill each mushroom with 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture.
Microwave, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes.
Check and turn after 2 minutes.
Makes 12 appetizers.

title: peach pie
directions: Layer peaches in unbaked pie crust. Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until peaches are soft.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with your hands.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese together and spread over cooled crust.
Beat the instant pudding and milk until thick and spread over the second layer.
Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip and slices of lemon.
A very pretty as well as delicious dessert.

title: marinated corn salad
directions: Remove husks from corn and cook in boiling water for 10 minutes or microwave until done.
Cut corn from cobs.
Combine corn and next 5 ingredients.
Set aside. Combine oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: layered shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, spices and mayonnaise.
Spread in a circle on a plate.
Cover with cocktail sauce.
Layer 3/4 pound of chopped shrimp.
Layer the remaining ingredients.
Garnish with remaining whole shrimp. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: curry pate
directions: Blend curry powder into softened cream cheese.
Add sherry. Mix well and cover.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Shape into small loaf.
Top with chutney and sprinkle with green onions. Serve with small crackers.

title: clams casino
directions: Steam clams until open; separate into halves.
Mix peppers, onion, Tabasco sauce and lemon.
Put pepper mixture onto each clam.
Top each clam with bacon and cheese.
Pop into oven for a few minutes until cheese melts.

title: wedding punch
directions: Pour 1 quart boiling water over sugar and citric acid and dissolve.
Add pineapple, orange and lemon juices.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: diane's cookies
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: frankfurter pie with mashed potatoes
directions: Cut wieners diagonally into 1-inch pieces.
Saute in oil in a large skillet for 5 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon; drain and reserve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix together margarine and shortening.
Then add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix together cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add this to first mixture while adding milk and vanilla. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: lima beans 'n dumplins
directions: Put lima beans, butter, sugar, tomato, salt and pepper in a pot.
Bring to a boil.

title: ham ball
directions: Chill ingredients in refrigerator for several hours; form into ball and roll in pecans.

title: aunt robin's orange salad(child-approved)
directions: Combine all ingredients and enjoy!

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together with your hands.
Roll into small balls about an inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in freezer bag.
When needed, place on cookie sheet and bake frozen at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: chopped beef cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: almost-pornographic dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise and lay them flat, "longwise," in a layer (frosting-side down) in a rectangular baking dish.
Cut bananas in half crosswise, then cut each part in half lengthwise. Lay bananas over Twinkies, in the same direction.
Mix instant pudding according to package directions and pour quickly over bananas and Twinkies (it sets quickly, so you need to move pretty fast).
Let set in refrigerator for about 5 minutes.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding and top with crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: roast duck
directions: Soak duck overnight in chilled salt water.
Boil 20 minutes in salt water.
Peel apples and chop.
Stuff body cavity with chopped apples.
Place orange slices on breast and hold with toothpicks. Cover duck with sweet and sour sauce.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cook green pepper, onion and celery until limp.
Add to sausage.
Mix rice, soups, mushrooms and liquid together.
Add to sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Last 5 minutes of cooking, add cheese to top and melt.

title: stromboli
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, and yeast.
Add water, milk, and butter.
Beat on low until well combined.
Turn onto a well-floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic 6-8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: easy company chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Pat dry.
Place in single layer in baking dish.
Sprinkle mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Can serve with rice.

title: ranch chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery and pineapple spears.
Separately combine salad dressing mix with mayonnaise and reserved pineapple juice. Add to chicken mixture and toss well to coat.
Chill.

title: old fashioned apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°.
In a large bowl combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add apple slices and mix until apples are evenly coated.
Spoon into pie shell.

title: cherry or blueberry topped cheese pie
directions: Beat together the cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Top with canned cherries or blueberries and chill well before serving.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan. Beat sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add bananas.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool.
Wrap in wax paper or foil.
Refrigerate.
Keeps moist at least a week.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and Kitchen Bouquet.
Form into 36 meatballs.
Brown lightly in small amount of oil.
Remove from pan.
Drain off grease.
Add soup to the pan and mix with drippings from meat balls.
Add 3/4 can of water to make a gravy. Add a drop of Kitchen Bouquet to darken.
Return meat balls to pan.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: grandma gerardi's rice pudding
directions: Rice:
Bring water to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover on low heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until water absorbs.

title: meat loaf parmesan
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and milk.
Add meat, egg substitute, Worcestershire sauce, salt, cheese, green pepper, onion and garlic salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken paprika
directions: In large Dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat and add onion and green peppers.
Saute until limp.
Add paprika and saute over 5 minutes.
(Secret is sauteing paprika long enough to release flavor.)
Add chicken and salt and then chicken stock. Cover and simmer until tender, about 40 minutes.
Turn chicken once.
Mix in flour and milk and stir until sauce is thickened. Reduce heat; add sour cream.
Mix in well and heat through.
Do not boil or sour cream will curdle.
Serve over dumpling or noodles.

title: nassau grits
directions: Cook grits by package directions.
Fry bacon and drain.
Brown onions and pepper in bacon drippings.
Add ham and tomatoes and cook down.
Mix with grits.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with crumbled bacon.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cajun style red beans and brown rice
directions: Rinse and soak beans overnight.
Cook everything together, except turkey ham, for one hour.
Add turkey ham and cook 1 1/2 hours more.

title: sunflower buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine buttermilk, egg, water, vanilla and butter in a small bowl, stirring well.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: roy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on a buttered pan and bake at 350° or 375° for about 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: spinach salad with oriental dressing
directions: Remove stems of spinach and rinse. Mix remainder of ingredients; pour over spinach. Add fried oysters or chopped bacon (optional).

title: greek chicken(serves 12)
directions: Pound breasts thin.
Mash olives, artichokes, Feta, 2 to 4 tablespoons oil, salt and pepper in bowl with pastry blender. Spread about 4 tablespoons of mixture on each breast.
Roll breast and secure with toothpick.
Heat remaining oil in heavy skillet. Place chicken breast in oil and brown on all sides.
Remove breasts from pan, add remaining 5 ingredients.
Stir and cook 10 minutes. Pour this sauce over chicken breasts.
Cook in 350° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with linguine, lots of good Chardonnay and a great big salad and crusty French bread.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour sugar over cranberry sauce and set aside.
Mix together celery, nuts and apples and drained pineapple.
Set aside.
Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over cherry jello mix.
Add enough water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1/2 cup.
Add this to jello.
Mix jello, sauce and fruit mixture together.
Chill until firm.

title: snacker crackers
directions: Line a 12 x 17-inch jelly roll pan with foil and grease it. Break crackers along scored markings to make 48 quarters.
Arrange these in one tight layer (they'll just fit).
Sprinkle evenly with chopped nuts.
In small saucepan, combine butter and sugar.
Bring to boil, then cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour evenly over crackers and nuts.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes.
Cool, then peel off the foil.

title: peach yogurt breakfast drink
directions: Place peaches and juice in blender.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Serve immediately over ice in tall glasses.
Makes 5 servings.

title: anywhere salad
directions: Blend ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Chill for several hours.
Serve; goes with anything at lunch or dinner.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered.

title: chocolate chip pan cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients together (except cookie dough) until smooth. In 9 x 13-inch pan smooth 1/2 roll of chocolate chip cookie dough. Pour cheese mixture onto cookie dough.
Top cheese mixture with other half of chocolate chip cookie dough that has been thinly sliced.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip mocha bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine coffee and water.
Add cake mix, sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla to coffee mixture; beat until smooth.
Stir in 2 cups chocolate chips.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until edges begin to pull away from side of pan.
Take 1 cup chocolate chips; pour on top of baked bars.
Wait 3 minutes, then spread to frost.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with garlic powder and marinate overnight in buttermilk.
Combine all other ingredients and dredge chicken. Spray baking pan or dish with cooking spray.
Place chicken in pan and bake at 425°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until done.

title: heath candy frosting
directions: Whip cream and add syrup slowly until mixed.
Fold in crushed bars.
Split angel food cake into 3 layers.
Fill layers and frost.
Enough for 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: diann's biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter. Place Karo and sugar in butter and mix well. Place pecans over this and sprinkle cinnamon according to pkg.

title: sauce hollandaise
directions: Melt the butter.
To the egg yolks, add the lemon juice and a teaspoon of cold water, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Mix continuously at low temperature.
Add the butter little by little while mixing until it thickens and becomes creamy.
This sauce is ideal for vegetables and broiled fish.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all canned vegetables. Combine in a large mixing bowl with green pepper, onion and celery.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, salt, vegetable oil, cider vinegar and paprika.
Mix well. Pour liquid mixture over vegetables and marinate at least 12 hours before serving.
Keeps well refrigerated up to 1 week.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Melt oleo in 11 x 13 baking dish.
Spread rice evenly over the pan.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup over all. Mix soup with milk and water and pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 325 for 2 1/2 hours.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Melt these together.
Beat in 3-4 cup powdered sugar 1 cup ground walnuts.

title: haystacks
directions: Heat chips until melted.
Stir in nuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Combine with butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with topping (2 cups of crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter, mixed). Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: Choose your favorite vegetables and cook in butter until tender.
Add soups and water, parsley and a few drops of hot sauce.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in shredded cheese, milk and sherry.
Do not boil.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel and grate carrots.
Peel and chop peaches.
Add sugar and raisins.
For dressing, mix the mayonnaise and slaw dressing together and add to other ingredients.

title: spencer's chili
directions: Soak beans in 6 cups of water overnight; drain.
In 6-quart pot, bring to a boil the presoaked pinto and kidney beans, 8 cups water, olive oil, bay leaf and lentils.
Simmer, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Add green pepper, carrots, onion, fresh tomato (canned at next step), chili powder, cumin, garlic, basil, oregano and thyme. Cover and simmer another 1/2 hour; stir occasionally.

title: pineapple lemon delight
directions: Chill canned milk in refrigerator overnight.
Crush cookies into crumbs; use half of them to line an oblong pan.
Save the rest to put on top.

title: spinach artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter in frying pan and cook spinach until it is thawed. Add cream cheese and stir until it is melted.
Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Place artichoke hearts in a greased, flat casserole.
Put spinach on top and cover with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Good with beef or pork.

title: three bean bake
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir sauteed onions with remaining ingredients, except bacon, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with bacon.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: brisket - baked
directions: Place foil on bottom of large roasting pan, big enough to cover all the meat.
Pour ingredients over meat, then wrap. Cook in oven about 3 hours at 350°.
Cool; skim off fat.
Slice meat and return to oven for another hour.
Meat should be soft. More soda and ketchup can be added for last hour if desired.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place mustard seed, garlic, hot pepper, dill and cucumbers in jars.
Bring vinegar, water and canning salt to a rolling boil and pour over stuffed jars until full.
Seal.
Place jars in pot of water and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; beat in the egg.
Stir in sour milk and bananas.
Then stir in dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add the nuts.
Turn into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Cool and eat or it freezes nicely.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: broccoli cheese and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until fluffy.
In a casserole dish, arrange the broccoli and rice in layers.
Start with a layer of broccoli, then a layer of rice and so forth.
Cover each layer with the Cheddar cheese sauce.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and butter until creamy.
Add beans and blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, then at 350° until knife comes out clean in middle.

title: mud or dirt
directions: Cream in one bowl butter and cream cheese.
Mix together pudding and milk, then add vanilla, Cool Whip and sugar.
Mix everything together.
Crush Oreos, except for one cookie.
Put one cookie on bottom of pot to cover the hole.
Layer cookies and mixture starting with cookie and ending with cookie.
Add flowers.

title: make-ahead potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Mix mashed potatoes with cream cheese, sour cream and seasonings to taste.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: microwave and oven stuffed potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes all over with fork.
Arrange in microwave dish and microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes, turning halfway through until tender.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Halve potatoes and scoop out insides.
Leave 1/4-inch shell.
Mash cooked potatoes with cottage cheese in bowl.
Stir in ham, Cheddar, onions, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese and spread over first mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: berlin scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and save 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Add spinach and heat through.
In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, combine dry sauce mix, water and milk according to box directions.
Omit butter. Stir in potatoes, bacon and spinach mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, and water together until yeast is dissolved. Add rest of ingredients.
Let rise until double, punch down, make into loaves and let rise until above pans.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
